title: "out of this world" lemon bars
directions: Combine the flour, butter and powdered sugar; blend with pastry blender.
Press into greased 8 x 8-inch square pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces and place in pot over open fire or 480°.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Recipe is for 3,800 people.
If you expect more than 3,800 people, add 2 rabbits, but most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: buster bars
directions: Place Oreo cookies and melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze 1 hour.
Spread ice cream.
Freeze.
Melt powdered sugar, butter, evaporated milk and chocolate chips.
Boil 8 minutes. Cool.
Sprinkle peanuts on ice cream and pour sauce over nuts. Freeze.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts and flavoring. Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 65 minutes.
Leave in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: strawberry pie(low calorie)
directions: Mix graham crackers, Sweet 'N Low and margarine together in pie pan.
Cook 5 minutes at 350° (cool).

title: chewy granola bites
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving or day ahead, into large bowl, measure flour, sugar, margarine or butter, orange juice, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and egg.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
With spoon, stir in granola cereal, raisins and oats.

Preheat oven to 350°. Drop dough by rounded tablespoons, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets. With fingers, smooth mounds slightly. Bake cookies 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned. With pancake turner, remove cookies to wire racks to cool. Store cookies in tightly covered container. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed wrapped jalapenos
directions: Cut jalapenos in half lengthwise and de-seed, as many an you would like.
Rinse, dry and stuff with cream cheese.
Add fajita meat or shrimp if desired.
Wrap bacon around each one and secure with toothpick.
Broil in the oven or cook on the grill outside.

title: orange salad
directions: Pour crushed pineapple undrained in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool, but don't let it gel.
Add cottage cheese, mandarin oranges (drained) and finally fold in the whipped topping. Pile into a pretty serving dish and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: best potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, celery seed, dill, onion flakes, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes and eggs; mixing lightly. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Put dill
seed	in
bottom of jars.
Wash cucumbers and cut into
small
strips
and
pack in jars.
Put on top garlic salt and alum powder.
Boil vinegar, water, salt and turmeric. Pour over cucumbers and seal while hot.	Chill before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Use dark bread or French bread for bowl and to dip.
A loaf of vegetable bread is very good.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix butter, egg and sugar; beat well.
Add dates and water to mixture, then flour to which the soda has been added.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breast, skin side up, on board.
With meat mallet, slightly pound each to 1/4-inch thick.
Season with salt. Place a ham slice and cheese stick on each breast.
Tuck in sides; roll jelly roll fashion, pressing to seal; tie securely.
Coat with flour; lightly brown in butter.
Place rolls in baking dish.

title: graham nut bread(from brown sugar bag)
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, baking powder, salt and nuts in a mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well.
Stir in milk, oil and grated orange rind.
Combine dry ingredients and egg mixture. Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing. Finish cooling on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in oil in a large Dutch oven until tender. Add tomatoes and next 3 ingredients.
Empty 1 can of beans into container of electric blender.
Blend beans until smooth. Add to tomato mixture with remaining can of beans.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes or to desired consistency.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: garden pea casserole
directions: Use a 2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Drain 1 can peas with pearl onions.
Pour into casserole and level.
Spread 1 can cream of celery soup over peas.
Sprinkle 1 small jar pimentos and then layer with water chestnuts that have been drained.
Sprinkle at least 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Melt margarine in frypan and using potato masher, crush 1 stack of Ritz crackers in margarine. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes, covered, and uncovered for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: baked oysters
directions: Finger each oyster so as to find and
remove any bits of shell.
Wash oysters but do not let stand in water.
Drain.
Mix salt and pepper with bread crumbs.
Melt butter, but do not brown. Add seasoned crumbs to butter.
Dip each oyster into crumb mixture and then into diluted egg and again into crumb mixture.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Heat butter in medium skillet.
Cook onion rings in butter until yellow.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Lower heat to simmer.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until vegetables are tender. Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pecans, together in mixer and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Sprinkle cut-up pecans over top of pies.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and boil hard for 1 minute. Take off of heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: summer slush
directions: Mix and boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Freeze and serve with ginger ale.

title: choco-krispie cookies
directions: Chocolate Abstract Designs:
Fill a pastry decorating bag fitted with a small tip with melted chocolate. Drizzle design on wax paper.
Freeze until firm.
Let come to room temperature; gently lift off design.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Pour Kahlua over warm brownies; cut into squares and layer in large bowl.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed together.
Pour over cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Let stand overnight, then put in freezer bags.
Freeze.

title: potato burger pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add eggs, potato, tomato sauce, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, salt and pepper; mix well. Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: crunchy muffins
directions: Add first 6 ingredients together.
In another bowl, put bananas, yogurt, eggs and vanilla together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fold together.
Don't overstir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken nuggets
directions: In a skillet, saut green pepper and onion in oil until crisp-tender; remove and keep warm. Add broth, syrup, vinegar and soy sauce to the skillet; bring to a boil. Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set aside. Combine cornstarch and juice, mixing until smooth. Gradually add to broth mixture. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Add green pepper, onion, chicken nuggets and pineapple chunks. Serve over hot rice.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together both soups, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper, onion and all seasonings.
Fold in potatoes. Spoon into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish and sprinkle with sesame seed and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for 2 hours.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Use part of margarine to grease casserole dish.
Place all ingredients in dish and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy rolls
directions: Melt oleo in hot water.
Add cold water, sugar, salt and yeast.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Stir in 3 cups of flour. Cover and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Make out rolls and let rise 1 1/2 or 2 hours, depending on temperature.
Cook at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Freeze.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of an oblong pan with a layer of graham crackers. Mix together vanilla pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over the graham crackers; place another layer of graham crackers over the pudding layer.
Spread the chocolate icing on top.
Place in the refrigerator and let chill.

title: devilishly delicious eggs
directions: Simmer equal parts of Pace picante sauce and honey in a saucepan until thickened. Add bite size cubes of cooked chicken or turkey breast (plain or smoked), cooked shrimp or 1/4-inch slices of smoked sausage.
Heat through and serve in a chafing dish or a shallow dish with wooden picks.

title: german icing
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a medium size pan.
Cook, stirring until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and nuts.

title: barbecue
directions: Place potatoes (do not peel) and carrots in 5-quart slow cooker. Place meat on top. Sprinkle with salt. Combine the barbecue sauce with catsup, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Stir well and pour over meat. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours or until meat is tender.

title: nutty banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.
Serves 4.

title: coconut tarts
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add salt, vanilla and almond.
Beat eggs slightly with fork; add to butter mixture.
Add coconut; blend well by hand.
If mixture is too loose, add more coconut. Refrigerate until ready to fill tart shells.
(This can be made a day ahead of baking, as can the pastry.)

title: seven layer salad
directions: Add a little sugar (2 tablespoons) to Miracle Whip.
Layer veggies, one after another, then top with Miracle Whip, then add cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to mix.

title: gravy-baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in shortening; pour off drippings.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: green pepper hot dish
directions: Brown the ground chuck with the onions. Add all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Serves 8.

title: homemade peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together: box of cake mix, crisco, peanut butter, and eggs. Mix well. Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet and cool. Make a cookie sandwich by spreading cream cheese frosting on the flat side of one cookie and topping with the flat side of another.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Place cherries in square cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Top with melted oleo and sprinkle with grated coconut and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned.

title: sauteed string beans with mushrooms
directions: Cut the tips from the string beans and, if too long, cut in halves.
Saute mushrooms and onions until tender in butter or oil. Cover pan and cook on low until tender.
Do not overcook, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix the frozen juices as directed on can, then add the sugar dissolved in water.
Add 7-Up and bananas and serve.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In a bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat.
Mix in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and stir.
Mix in chocolate chips. Spread into a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese-filled pasta shells
directions: Cook shells as package indicates.
Drain. Combine Ricotta, Parmesan and spinach. Fill shells with cheese mixture.
Place in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x
2-inch baking dish.
Combine tomato paste with 2 cans of water.
Pour over and around shells. Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed corn on cob
directions: Combine butter and seasoning. Spread over corn. Yields 8 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and slice	apples; add enough water to cook apples until soft.
Press
through
sieve
and
measure.
Combine all ingredients and cook about	1
to
1 1/2 hours or until thick. Stir often	to
prevent
scorching.
Pour into sterilized jars within 1/2-inch of	top.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Gradually add milk to flour and when smooth, add eggs and salt.
(Best when with an egg beater.)
Pour melted butter or beef drippings 1/2-inch thick over bottom of 2 bread pans.
Pour half of mixture in each pan.
Bake in a hot oven, 400°, for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.
Cut in squares and serve with roast beef.

title: choling's baked beans
directions: In baking pan or shallow dish, combine beans, brown sugar, mustard and onion.
Mix well.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: french garlic chicken
directions: Finely mince or press 4 cloves garlic in a small dish with lemon juice.
Rub the mixture over chicken or put minced garlic and lemon juice in a large Ziploc and add the chicken.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well. Serve with chilled fruit.

title: baked beans
directions: Pick over beans; cover with water overnight.
Parboil and rinse.
Put in dish over salt pork.
Add all ingredients.
Cover with water plus 1 inch.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, then at 250° for 6 hours.

title: fried won tons
directions: Brown and drain ground pork, set aside.
Break apart cabbage and boil just until tender (not soft, do not overcook).
Remove from
hot water and cool with cold water.
Roll cabbage leaves up together and squeeze out water from cabbage by hands.
Chop up cabbage and squeeze again.
Chop up the garlic, green onions and ginger.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put 1 tablespoon into each won ton wrapper.
Fold into triangle. Seal edges with water and flour.
Fry in sesame oil until golden brown.

title: seafoam chews
directions: Sift together and set aside the flour, baking powder and soda. Blend together shortening, sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add flour mix, egg yolks, vanilla and milk.
Press dough into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package chocolate chips.
Beat until stiff 2 egg whites.
Beat in gradually remaining 1 cup brown sugar.
Spread meringue over dough and top with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy french icing
directions: Boil sugar and water a few minutes to make syrup.
Mix confectioners sugar and egg until well blended.
Add sugar-water syrup a little at a time, beating well.
Blend in Crisco and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: rosy candy apple dip
directions: You will also need 8 wooden sticks.

title: marshmallows(by elva sorenson)
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to a medium hard ball (231°). Put gelatine in mixing bowl in cold water.
Pour hot mix over gelatine mix and beat about 10 minutes (or until it begins to work up on beaters).
Then add egg whites and continue beating until it thickens again, 5 minutes or more.
Add coloring and flavoring, if desired (1 teaspoon vanilla, raspberry, almond) and pour in buttered 9 x 9-inch square pan and let stand in fridge at least 2 hours.
Put on a cold damp tea towel and cut into desired pieces. Roll in coconut (fine), chopped nuts or cracker crumbs, if desired.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as directed.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling point, stirring.
Then reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese and the macaroni. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake 15 minutes.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in pastry shell at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 325° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: school lunch
directions: Mix the 2 cups knowledge with 1 pint of understanding.

Blend in a dash of thoughtfulness and add a yolk of loyalty; stir in a pinch of inspiration. When this is done, blend in the 1 1/2 tablespoons devotion and a generous pinch of humor. Add to the other mix. Place in pan of imagination. Bake at a temperature of gentleness and serve with love!!!!!!

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa and salt; cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in 1 beaten egg. Press mixture evenly on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 25 minutes.

title: hot cakes
directions: Place oats and buttermilk in a mixing bowl; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar.
Beat eggs; add butter and stir into oat mixture.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt; add all at once to oat mixture.
Stir lightly with wooden spoon only until combined; do not beat.
Spoon batter onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Yield: 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: easy variety cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, egg, oil and water. Beat until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are set.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Take strawberries out of freezer 1 hour before you make ice cream.
Pour 1 cup strawberries into container with sugar and cream; stir with spoon.
Close container and put in freezer overnight.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Do not make pudding.
Mix above ingredients well and chill.

title: date nut cake
directions: Pour hot water over first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Combine last four ingredients in a large iron skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add nuts to mixture which will crystallize as soon as it sticks to nuts.
Pour on baking sheet and cook in 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: one dish meal
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until almost done.
Add cooked macaroni, tomatoes, kidney beans, salt and pepper.
Layer this with cheese in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
A baked potato and crisp salad makes a complete meal.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Place beef in heated oil in heavy sauce kettle.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook until beef is brown.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir. Cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add water, tomatoes, beef flavor base, bay leaves, thyme and basil.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add onion, celery, carrots, potatoes, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until beef and vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Sprinkle peas over stew and serve with biscuits or steamed rice.
Serves 10.

title: baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put chicken pieces into pan.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Add water.
Slice onion and green pepper; place on top of chicken.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 400°.

title: low-fat bread pudding
directions: Toast bread that has been buttered.
Soak raisins in boiling water for 5 minutes, then drain.
Tear bread into small pieces and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle on the raisins.
Scald milk.
Stir in the 1/3 cup sugar.
Beat eggs slightly and add to warm milk. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour milk mixture over bread and raisins and let stand about 10 minutes.
If toasted bread floats, push it down.
When the bread is well soaked, mix the 2 tablespoons of sugar and the cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
This may be served hot or cold.

title: english butter toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange saltines in a single layer in bottom of pan.
Melt butter and sugar in medium pan over medium heat.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over crackers; spread evenly.
Bake for 5 minutes.
If crackers shift, rearrange with fork.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes, or until top is set.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels on top.
When soft, spread out.
Sprinkle nuts over chocolate.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: strawberry banana drink
directions: Blend in blender.
Each serving contains 70 calories.

title: the trawler's famous crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with crackers.
If you prefer a little extra tang, don't be afraid to add more horseradish or French dressing.

title: every bake bean
directions: Brown hamburg.
Drain grease.
Add everything else.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill before serving.
If necessary, add more clam juice to make right consistency to dip.
Serve with Fritos.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well. Rinse with cool water to cool quickly.
Drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients and toss lightly but well.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: french and english salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Keep in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add eggs, butter and milk.
Bake in unbaked pie shell in slow oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook soup, rice and water for 7 minutes.
Add sausage, bell pepper, celery and onions.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: quick quik stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add soup mix, tomato soup, mushroom soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Line oblong pan with bread slices.
Place remaining ingredients in pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test as for custard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and stuffing mix.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese and then stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix dry cake mix and nuts.
Line bottom of pan.
Put pie filling in, then chop up butter on top of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook all butter, margarine, sugar and corn syrup into a syrup until "hard
ball".
Remove
from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
This
will
foam.
Pour
over
popped corn; mix. Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Let
cool
and
break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Bring to a good boil.
Add corn, cheese and eggs.
Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Add sugar, water, salt and syrup in microwavable dish; cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add peanuts; cook 10 minutes.
Take out of microwave; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and food coloring. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: antipasto tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed on package.
Drain; rinse with cold water.

In a large bowl, combine tortellini, salami, Provolone cheese, corn, spinach, artichoke hearts and 1 cup of the olives. In a small bowl, combine salad dressing, mustard and 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese; blend well.
Pour dressing over salad; blend well. Pour dressing over salad; toss gently.
Top with remaining olives and Parmesan cheese.
Cover; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with pimiento before serving, if desired.
Makes 8 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and salt.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook to soft ball stage (235° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool mixture until lukewarm (110°), then add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until candy begins to lose high gloss.
Turn into buttered 8-inch pan.
Score with sharp knife into squares.
Cool. When completely cold, cut squares all the way through.
Makes 2 pounds.
Will keep 2 weeks in a tightly covered container.

title: shrimp fondue
directions: Chop shrimp and set aside.
Place remaining ingredients in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until blended.
Fold in shrimp. Serve hot in a fondue dish.
Surround with chunks of French bread.

title: pizza bear
directions: Toast the bread in the toaster.
Cut a bear shape from the toast with teddy bear cookie cutter.
Using a spoon, spread pizza sauce on your bear.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on bear.
Top with pepperoni.
On a tray, microwave for 15 to 20 seconds or until cheese is melted.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup white flour and raisins and/or nuts; set aside. Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add soda, salt and molasses until blended.
Mix in flours and milk, then flour-nut-raisins mixture; blend well.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Raise 15 minutes. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli topped tuna bake
directions: Prepare macaroni per instructions; drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz.
In a large bowl, combine cream of mushroom soup, milk and remaining Cheez Whiz.
Stir in tuna, pepper and macaroni. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Remove from oven.
Arrange broccoli spears in spoke fashion on top of macaroni mixture and top with reserved Cheez Whiz.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes more until heated.
To make 4 servings, use half of each ingredient except broccoli.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter in a medium saucepan until tender.
Combine soup mix, half and half and pepper; pour into saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in broccoli and eggs; pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Mix raisins with boiling water.
Stir and set aside.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and pork and beans until beans are broken (will not break up small but will be fine anyway).
Add flour and rest of dry ingredients to bean mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drain raisins, add and mix well.
Pour into 3 well-greased bread pans. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: incredible egg macaroni salad
directions: Prepare Kraft dinner as directed on package, leaving out butter.
Add rest of ingredients, except 1 egg (not chopped).
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Garnish with remaining egg, sliced.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat; drain off any fat.
Add all ingredients, except cabbage, green beans and spaghetti.
Bring to boiling, then lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cabbage, green beans and spaghetti.
Bring to boiling again and simmer until spaghetti is tender.
If you prefer a thinner soup, add extra broth or water. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and soda in a bowl.
Heat the margarine, cocoa, marshmallows and Coke to boiling point; mix with sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured pan.

title: andes candies chocolaty chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugars until light.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Gradually stir in flour mixture, then Andes, walnuts and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven for 7 to 8 minutes, or until brown.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat together.
Heat a round wrought iron grill to medium heat.
Spray with a vegetable coating or use melted butter.
(If using butter, replenish butter between pancakes.) Pour a scant 1/2 cup batter in the center of the round grill.
Pick up the grill and turn it in a circular motion until the batter is evenly distributed on pan.
When the top of the batter loses its shine and seems dry or dull, loosen pancake all the way around and flip over, cooking briefly on other side.
Remove to a platter and cover.
Repeat.
The pancakes will stay warm and soft for 20 minutes under the cover when all are cooked.
Add your fruit in a line down the center of a pancake and roll into a log.
Serve as the Swede's do, filled with lingonberry sauce or cranberry sauce. Or serve filled with applesauce as the German's do.
Or roll them plain and serve maple or fruit syrup.
This recipe makes about eight 10-inch pancakes.
Serves 3 to 4.
This recipe is easily doubled or halved.

title: chicken breasts florentine
directions: Cook spinach per package directions.
Drain well.
Place chicken with salt, celery, onion and 1 cup water in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from broth.
Reserve 1 cup.
Discard vegetables.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine beef, bread, eggs and milk.
Add spices and salt. Stir in 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce; form into 12 thick patties. Wrap a bacon slice around each patty (sides); secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes on wire rack, until desired doneness is reached.
Baste frequently with remaining barbecue sauce the last 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll into marble size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over hot water.
Dip each ball and place on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Chill and store in refrigerator.

title: taco soup
directions: Add the ingredients to the hamburger that has been browned. Cook 15 minutes with cover on pot.
Garnish with shredded cheese, sour cream and taco chips.

title: gooey chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients - just dump it all together - no creaming, etc.
Add nuts and chips and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a Bundt or angel cake pan.
After cake is cool, sprinkle top with slivered almonds or powdered sugar.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar into a bowl.
Add shortening, eggs and 1/2 cup bananas.
Stir to combine, then beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining bananas and lemon juice.
Beat 2 minutes more; fold in the nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: vegetable-potato soup
directions: Lightly spray large soup pot or Dutch oven with nonfat cooking spray and heat over medium-high heat. Add potatoes, carrots and celery to pot; sprinkle vegetables with garlic and onion powder. Cook 2 to 3 minutes until heated.
Pour chicken broth in pan and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender and soft.
Add tomatoes, peas, beans, dill weed and pepper to vegetables.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until heated through.

title: sarkis' peach butter
directions: Wash peaches.
Peel, quarter and pit.
Place 3 cups at a time into blender.
Cover.
Blend until smooth.
Repeat process. Measure 11 cups.
Place in crock-pot.
Stir in lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cook uncovered on High for 9 hours, stirring twice. Stir in sugar.
Cook uncovered 2 more hours, stirring several times.
Pour into hot, sterilized 1/2-pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims; adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
(Start time when water returns to boiling.) Makes 8 one-half pints.

title: orange - peach marmalade(heritage cookbook)
directions: Mix peaches and 2 cups sugar together and let stand.
Boil oranges and 2 cups water for 1 hour.
Add peach mixture to orange plus 2 cups of sugar.
Boil 1/2 hour or until thick.
Remove from stove and add cherries, cut into small pieces, also 2 or 3 peach seeds, cut thin.
Pour into glasses and seal.

title: spicy fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add chicken pieces, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Drain chicken, discarding buttermilk mixture.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture, shaking off any excess.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Pour oil to depth of 1/2-inch into a large skillet; heat to 350°.
Add 1/3 of chicken and fry 20 to 25 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Repeat procedure with remaining chicken.
Garnish, if desired.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan, then boil your noodles in pot until tender.
Add ground beef in pot.
Add your tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce and salt.
Boil for about 5 minutes, then take, put in oven and bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Take out and serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted butter or margarine, 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Combine cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups sugar, 5 eggs and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well and pour into crust and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Let cool and then top with 1 can cherry pie filling.

title: "any" fruit cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk.
In deep dish 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in peaches and juice.
Dot with stick butter. Then pour flour mixture in middle of peaches.
Bake at 350° or until cobbler is golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Any fruit can be used.

title: 4-layer pie
directions: Mix.
Press in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: easy cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion and celery.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add carrots, broccoli and broth.
Cover and bring to boil, separating broccoli with fork. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add milk; bring to simmer.
Stir in cheese, stirring until melted.
Pour soup into ovenproof casserole or individual soup bowls.
Place cheese wedges on French bread; float on top of soup.
Place under a broiler just long enough to melt and turn a delicate brown.
Seres 6 to 8.

title: foolproof pie crust for italian cheesecake
directions: With a fork, mix together the first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
With hands, mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling into desired shape.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain, arranging half in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Saut onions in butter until tender. Blend in cream cheese. Stir in cottage cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper. Spread half atop of noodles. Combine soup, milk and wine, then stir in shrimp and crab. Spread one-half over cottage cheese layer. Repeat layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 350°, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 2 to 3 minutes more. Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix together.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together.
Pack firmly into buttered loaf pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk cheese loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in cheese. Make a well in the center of mixture. Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil. Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened. Spoon batter into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: southwest soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add the 5 cans, undrained. Mix well. Heat on stove or in a crock-pot. Right before serving, add in the cheese and melt.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients together.
Parboil carrots and slice. Spray pan with Pam.
Layer carrots, 1 onion and peppers with sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over carrots and refrigerate 3 or 4 days.

title: sunny coconut cake
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and orange juice.
Beat in coconut. Cover and refrigerate.
In another bowl, combine cake mix, gelatin, water, oil and eggs, mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely. Split cakes in half, horizontally.
Set aside 1 cup of coconut filling.
Spread remaining filling between cake layers. Refrigerate.
Beat cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold into reserved filling.
Frost top and sides of cake.
Garnish with oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer, except raisins and pecans. Add the raisins and pecans. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Use 4 (1 pound) coffee cans or 2 loaf pans.

title: cheese - vegetable soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water in a large saucepan.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender; drain.

title: tasty cheese appetizers
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients (except bread) and blend thoroughly.
Dip each bread chunk in mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight or freezer for later baking. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: linguine with garden clam sauce
directions: In a large skillet melt margarine over medium-high heat.
Add zucchini and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Combine clam sauce with enough water to equal 1 3/4 cups.
Stir in cornstarch until smooth. Add to skillet with bouillon cubes and clams.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 1 minute.
Toss with linguine and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage together with onions, peppers and celery.
Strain off excess fat.
Boil macaroni about 3/4 box. After noodles are done in a large bowl, mix meat and noodles.
Add in tomato sauce, whole tomatoes (mashed), 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with remaining Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Place in oven at 350°. Bake for 45 minutes.
Can be served with Brown 'N Serve rolls and toss salad.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Mash and blend ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water and 1 teaspoon salt to a boil.
Add macaroni and cook until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Put a layer of macaroni in a baking dish and cover with a layer of cheese.
Repeat.
Drip melted butter over the macaroni.
Combine eggs, milk and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour over macaroni and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine rice, water and bouillon cubes.
Cook as directed on box.
When rice is finished, add cooked broccoli.
Melt cheese with milk and butter, then add to mixture.
Stir well.
Serve hot as a casserole or cold as a summer salad.

title: george's bread seasoning
directions: Note:
Caraway seeds or sesame seeds may be substituted.

title: picante sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers coarsely.
Combine tomato mixture and remaining ingredients in a large pan or kettle.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Pour hot mixture in hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims and cover at once with metal lids and screw on tight.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yields 16 pints.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Combine buttermilk baking mix, milk and eggs in medium bowl. Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in chips.
Pour 2 tablespoons of batter onto hot, slightly greased griddle.
Cook until bubbles appear.
Turn.
Cook other side until lightly browned.
Serve warm with butter or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: nut crisp cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in 1/2 to 1 cup nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: company french toast
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add brown sugar and cinnamon. Cover with bread slices.
Beat eggs well. Add salt and milk.
Pour over bread.
Cover and let stand overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: not yo' mama's banana pudding
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 pan with bag of cookies. Combine milk and pudding mix; blend well. Combine cream cheese and condensed milk; mix smooth. Fold in whipped topping and add to pudding mixture. Pour all mixture over cookies and bananas. Cover with remaining cookies and refrigerate.

title: fast whole wheat bread
directions: Mix honey in lukewarm water.
Sprinkle yeast on top and let sit until frothy, about 5 minutes.
Mix flour and salt.
Pour yeast mixture in middle of flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in oiled bread pan.
Let rise about 20 minutes or just a little over the top of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, then enjoy.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish (Pyrex) that's been well greased.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
If too watery, uncover after 30 minutes.

title: never fail sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, shortening, baking powder, soda and salt as you would for pie crust.
Add eggs, vanilla, sugar and milk.
Stir well, then roll dough (1/4 of dough at a time) 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
(Do not let cookies brown on top.)
Can frost with powdered sugar icing with almond flavoring.

title: 3 corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is brown.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil. Whisk in Jell-O and pudding mixes. Return to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and cool completely. Fold in oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip. Pour into a serving bowl. Cover and chill for about 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Warm green beans in saucepan; add cream of mushroom soup, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour into glass bowl.
Sprinkle top with onions and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old virginia corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add corn.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and stir into corn mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in crushed pineapple and cover with sugar.
Pour on cherry pie filling and yellow cake mix.
Melt butter.
Add pecans and pour butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, then add sugar, salt, milk, hot water and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and bake 15 minutes at 450°, then at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers or cut in strips and let stand overnight in hot water.
Boil vinegar, sugar and spices for 5 minutes.
Pour over sliced cucumbers that have been packed in jars.
Seal. This makes 3 quarts or 6 pints.
Vinegar can be reheated.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Add chopped vegetables.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil until most of sugar is dissolved.
Marinate at least 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt bits in double boiler and add noodles.
Stir good and drop on waxed paper.
Chill and eat.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks stiff and lemon colored.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Set heat selector at 400°.
Drop spoonfuls into hot Crisco.
Fry 4 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with syrup.
(Dip in syrup.)

title: hong kong rice
directions: Brown
beef and onion in skillet over medium heat.
Add remaining
ingredients.
May
cover and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes
or
place	in
casserole
and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Dredge chicken in flour; brown in olive oil until golden. Season and place chicken in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add tomatoes to skillet and stir to deglaze pan.
Add salt, garlic, Accent, oregano, basil and pepper.
Spread mushrooms over chicken.
Pour tomato mixture over chicken and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour sherry over top.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with Fettucine Alfredo.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add cocoa.
Add eggs (well beaten), then the jam and buttermilk with soda dissolved in milk. Fold in flour, spices and vanilla.
Bake in large pan at 350°.

title: swingin-wings
directions: Cut off wing tips; break each chicken wing into 2 pieces.
Dip each chicken wing first into butter and then into combined cheese and garlic powder.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve at cocktail parties or luncheons.
Yields 5 servings.

title: apricot cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine margarine, granulated sugar and cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Blend in eggs, juice and rind.
Add combined flour and baking powder; mix well.
Chill.
Shape level measuring tablespoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Indent centers; fill with preserves. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mexican chili rice
directions: Crumble chips and place in serving dish. Heat chili. Add milk to soup; heat and place lettuce, tomatoes and onions on serving dish. Now place the rice on top of chips, then chili on top then soup, then top with lettuce, tomatoes and onions.

title: never fail brisket
directions: Season brisket to taste with onion powder, garlic powder and pepper.
Broil in pan for 10 minutes on each side.
Be careful not to burn meat.
Add 2 cups hot water to onion soup mix.
Add 12 ounces apricot jam and 1 cup ketchup.
Pour mixture over meat. Bake 3 hours at 350°.
Better if made the day before.
Freezes very well.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Crumble uncooked Ramen noodles and add to broccoli slaw. Add almonds and sunflower nuts. Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and seasoning mix together and pour over slaw. Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake confetti brownies
directions: In a bowl, mix together nuts, marshmallows, crumbs and sugar. In a saucepan, melt chocolate in evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat; add peppermint extract.
Reserve 1/2 cup chocolate mixture for frosting; add remainder to crumb mixture.
Stir until all crumbs are moistened. Turn into greased 8-inch square pan; press down.
Spread reserved chocolate mixture over top.
Chill until ready to serve.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch pieces.
Use nut half for garnish.
Yield:

title: chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken with spice.
Melt margarine in skillet, then put chicken in skillet.
Cook until done.

title: spud casserole
directions: Mix soups and corn together in large bowl.
Brown hamburger and cook until tender.
Add to soup mixture and pour over sliced potatoes in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and eat.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Soak bread crumbs and milk for 5 minutes in a large mixing bowl.
Combine meats, salt and eggs with bread crumbs and mix well.
Stir in onion, celery, green pepper, garlic and Worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Pack into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; shape to leave a fingers width between meat and pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 nine-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: tomatoes au gratin
directions: Cut 6 tomatoes in half crosswise.
Arrange them, cut side up in a lightly greased, shallow baking pan.
Toss fresh bread crumbs with melted butter or margarine.
Add sesame seed, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss to mix well.
Spoon bread crumbs mixture onto tomato halves.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until tender.
Serves 6.

title: heath bars
directions: Break crackers in squares and line the bottom of 2 pans (11 x 14-inch and 9 x 12-inch).
Cook until boiling margarine, butter and sugar.
Cook 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine both sugars, salt and milk in saucepan; bring to a full boil for 3 minutes (stirring frequently).
Test after each minute by dropping 1/4 teaspoon of mixture into small amount of cold water.
Will form easily into small ball when finished. Remove pan from heat; while stirring, add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Layer peppers, eggs and cheese in a 1 1/2 quart greased casserole dish.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Then spread buttered crumbs on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion.
Saute celery. Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glorified grahams
directions: Put crackers in baking pan.
Mix oleo (melted) and brown sugar.
Spread 1/2 over crackers and put nuts in remainder of mixture.
Put on top crackers, then bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until stiff.
Fold in crushed crackers and pecans.
Bake in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely. Top with Cool Whip.
Put filling over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: chili
directions: Combine onion and celery with about 1 cup of water; put in microwave for 10 minutes.
Put margarine in frypan.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper.
Brown thoroughly.
Add celery and onion.
Heat through.
Put rest of ingredients, except macaroni, in large kettle.
Heat through.
Cook your macaroni.
Add hamburger mixture and your cooked macaroni.
Simmer through for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese and mix until well blended and smooth.
Add pineapple, nuts and 7-Up.
Pour into dish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° to 375° for one hour. Seems better if frozen awhile.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Work in flour, sugar and salt. Blend until smooth. Chill until firm.
Roll dough very thin, then cut into 5-inch squares.
Fold into triangles.
Toss apples with seasoning to taste. Place apples onto half of each square.
Press edges to seal.
Bake in a 400° oven until dough is well puffed and brown, about 15 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Beat eggs. Heat milk and margarine together on low heat.

title: praline honey grahams
directions: Bring oil and sugar for 2 minutes.
Stirring, add nuts.
Line cookie sheet with graham crackers, about 1 1/2 packages.
Cover these with boiled mixture.
Bake for 10 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone.
Mix corn meal, water and eggs. If needed, add more water.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400° or until brown.
Melt butter and soup mix with chicken broth.
Crumble cornbread in pan with chicken mixture.
Then add diced onions, poultry seasoning, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Cook until brown.
Add water as needed to keep moist.
Feeds 50.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans with oil.
Do not flour pans. Mix all ingredients well; pour into pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in water to cover.

Drain. Prepare chicken stock by simmering chickens in 2 quarts water to which the whole onion, celery, carrot, parsley and bay leaves are added. Simmer until meat is tender. Remove chickens and cool. Remove meat and skin from bones and dice meat.
Strain broth and skim off fat.
Mix beans, chicken broth and 1 chopped onion. Cook until beans are just tender.
Heat oil in skillet. Add garlic and remaining chopped onion. Saute until tender and golden. Add this mixture and remaining ingredients to beans. Simmer 20 minutes. Add chicken and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans in hot water; drain.
Combine in large soup pot, beans, ham hock, carrots and 4 quarts of water.
Cover and cook slowly 3 to 4 hours or until beans are tender but not mushy. Toward end of cooking time, saute onion in butter or margarine 5 minutes, then add all to bean soup.
May add leftover diced ham also.
Taste mixture for seasoning.
Add salt and pepper if needed. Cook over moderate heat 10 minutes longer.
Serve in warmed bowls. Makes about 6 servings.

title: ants on a log
directions: Peel banana and cut in 1/2.
Now take peanut butter and spread over top of banana.
Sprinkle about 5 raisins on top of the peanut butter and enjoy.
Makes 2 servings.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Put all ingredients, except mushrooms, into a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes to develop flavor.
Add mushrooms and simmer 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally and gently until tender.
Cover and cool in liquid.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 3 days.

title: sinful salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Let cool and add bananas, pecans (optional), strawberries and pineapple; divide in 1/2.
Pour 1/2 mixture in a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Keep remaining 1/2 of mixture at room temperature.
Spread sour cream evenly over jello in pan.
Pour on remaining mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until done.
Dice.
Toss broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill before serving.

title: sesame crab rolls
directions: Melt cheese and margarine; cool slightly. Add crab meat and stir until cool. Flatten bread with rolling pin. Spread with crab meat mixture. Roll as for jelly roll. Dip in butter; roll in sesame seed. Freeze on baking sheet. Thaw for 15 minutes before serving. Cut into fifths. Broil for 5 minutes, turning once.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Layer biscuits, cheese, onion, pepper and sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk well. Roll on pastry sheet until very thin. Mix sausage and cheese well and spread over the pastry. Roll as for jelly roll. Chill and slice very thinly. Place on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake at 350° to 400° until lightly brown.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese and add drained Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix together and serve hot with nachos.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla, raisins and pineapple together. Stir into noodles and cottage cheese. Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°. After 25 minutes, lightly cover top with crushed corn flakes. You can also add chopped nuts if you like. Dot with butter or margarine and continue baking for another 30 minutes.

title: goof proof fudge
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Cook on high 2 minutes or until margarine melts.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Cool and slice.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix carrots and soup; bake in a 275° oven until bubbly. Spread onions over top; return to oven for 10 minutes, until browned.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Mix instant potatoes as directed.
Add all ingredients to potatoes.
Mix well!
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and let stand 5 minutes. Combine all ingredients to form dough.
Cover and raise 5 minutes. Then cover tightly and refrigerate for 1 hour.
With a tablespoon form biscuits on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.
The dough will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Stir in onion, sour cream, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper. Cover and reserve.
Heat remaining ingredients; simmer 5 minutes, uncovered.
Pour into pie plate. Dip each tortilla into sauce; coat both sides. Spoon 1/4 cup hamburger mixture onto each and roll.
Arrange in a 12 x 9-inch ungreased dish.
Pour remaining sauce over. Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with shredded cheese, lettuce, onion or lemon wedge, if desired.

title: frankie's breakfast scramble
directions: Melt butter in skillet on medium heat.
Place tortilla pieces in skillet until softened (not too long or they will get tough). Add eggs and scramble together.
When eggs are almost cooked, add as much cheese as desired.
Scramble until cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain. Alternate layers of noodles and cheese in deep casserole dish, adding the tablespoons of butter in between layers. In a small dish, mix eggs with a little milk and salt and pepper. Pour mixture over noodles and cheese. Then add more milk to almost the top of noodles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix all ingredients.
Form into 2 balls. Roll in pecans.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Place
in
separate layers in 2 quart casserole noodles and tomatoes.
Add
pepper
slices.
Sprinkle each layer with flour, salt
and pepper and grated cheese.
Cover with cut-up eggplant slices.
Pour
over
top
beef
broth
or
bouillon. Sprinkle with more grated cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Top with
cracker
crumbs.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.	Serves 6. Delicious one dish meal.

title: vegetable dip #2
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: krissy's yum yums
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave with 1 teaspoon oil.
Stir in cereal and peanuts.
Spread candy mixture on waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator.
When candy hardens, break into bite-size pieces.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla; mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and molasses, then add dry ingredients and cold water. Mix well.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Roll out and cut with large cookie cutter.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: the undescribable cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake (package directions).
In a medium saucepan combine pineapple with juice and sugar; cook over medium heat until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, pierce top with fork about 1 inch apart.
Pour on pineapple mixture and spread evenly on cake.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°, grease 12 (2 1/2 inch) muffin cups. Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Stir in rolled oats and sugar; set aside.
Combine milk, butter, egg and vanilla in a small bowl.
Stir milk mixture into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Stir in strawberries.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling each 2/3 full.
Bake 15 - 18 minutes or until lightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pasta with a twist(light choice)
directions: In small bowl, combine water, bouillon cubes and cornstarch; stir to blend.
In large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon margarine over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms, carrots, red pepper, garlic, basil and dried red pepper.
Stirring constantly, cook 2 minutes. Remove vegetables with slotted spoon.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon margarine; saute onion 3 minutes.
Re-stir cornstarch mixture and pour into skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Return vegetables to skillet; heat through.
Stir in lemon juice and macaroni.
Makes 4 servings. Per serving:
330 calories, 56 g carbohydrates, 9 g protein, 5 g polyunsaturated fat, 1 g saturated fat, 0 mg cholesterol, 400 mg sodium.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown burger; drain.
In a large pot or crock-pot, put burger and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water. Let cool. Mix in other ingredients and chill until firm.

title: mashed potato surprise
directions: Cook potatoes until soft; drain.
Add milk until creamy, then add butter and dressing.
Mix well.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and debone chicken; set aside.
Save broth.
Grate cheese.
Saute onion and peppers in butter.
In large pot, mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of cheese.
If real thick, add chicken broth until juicy.
Pour in large casserole dish; put rest of the cheese on top.
Bake in oven, about 375° to 400° until bubbly and golden brown on top.

title: easy broccoli bake(conventional method or microwave)
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces, cook and drain.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Stir in cooked broccoli and 1/2 can of onions.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly and continue beating.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix after each addition.
Add milk and mix. Add rest of ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned and done.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes. Serve hot.
(Can put a cinnamon stick in each cup.)

title: mary's pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix altogether and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: mushroom tarts
directions: Heat butter in skillet; add onion and cook until yellow.
Add mushrooms; cook about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle in seasonings and flour.
Stir.
Add sour cream; cook and stir until thickened. Cool.
Fill tarts and bake 10 to 15 minutes in 450° preheated oven.
Can be made ahead, baked or frozen and heated when needed. Makes 2 dozen tarts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 3 x 1-inch strips.
Brown strips in shortening in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Blend in flour, then tomato juice and mushroom stems and pieces, drained.
Cover; cook over low heat 1 hour, until meat is tender.
Stir in mixture of milk and lemon juice.
Heat until steaming, but do not boil. Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, milk, soup, pepper and half a can of fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch dish , uncovered.
Top with remaining can of fried onions and cook for 5 minutes longer.

title: low-fat fettuccine alfredo
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, prepare fettuccine as label directs, using 2 teaspoon salt in water; drain.
Keep warm.
In 5 quart saucepot, mix flour, pepper, ground nutmeg and 3/4 teaspoon salt; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove saucepot from heat.
Stir in fettuccine, grated Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley.
Toss to coat well.
Serve immediately garnished with parsley sprigs.
Makes 4 main dish servings.
Each serving contains 420 calories, 6 g fat and 13 mg cholesterol.

title: hocus pocus crispies
directions: Unroll crescents into 1 long rectangle; pinch and seal perforations.
Spread with butter.
Combine brown sugar, walnuts and cinnamon; sprinkle on butter.
Roll up and cut into 8 slices. Place slices on ungreased sheet.
Flatten each piece to 4 to 5-inch diameter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: colorado-mex out of fridge snack
directions: Place tortillas on microwave plate.
Spread with picante sauce (as you like).
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Heat in microwave for 30 seconds.
Fold from one side of circle 2 times, then fold over the sides toward center and then continue to fold.
Very hot out of microwave.
Easy and tasty.

title: fruit loaf(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350° or in 2 smaller loaf pans for 45 minutes.

title: briana's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add 1 tablespoon flour. Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Add flour and bananas alternately, reserving 1/2 cup flour.
With this, sift salt and baking powder and soda and mix with rest.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked boneless pork chops(makes 6 servings)
directions: Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dredge chops lightly in mixture.
Heat oleo and brown pork chops on both sides.
Transfer to shallow baking dish.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Cook until onion is soft and golden.
Blend in milk and cook until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Season with dash of salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; add juice of lemon.
Pour sauce over chops and bake covered for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add Ragu to ground beef.
Layer in casserole dish, beginning with meat sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers; end with meat sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and sour cream.
Sift flour and soda.
Add one egg, then flour, until you have used all.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan.

title: bob's moma's tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Put in refrigerator about 1 hour.
After you take it out, spread the Cool Whip on top. Serve.

title: sherbet-mandarin
directions: Drain mandarins and set aside the syrup.
Puree mandarins in blender.
Mix in the remaining ingredients and mandarin syrup. Freeze in ice cream maker or use freezer tray method.
Serves 6.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: *If nuts are omitted, add an additional 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips.

title: dulane cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and sugar.
Melt butter.
Add sweet milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in layers.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Remove from pan after cookie has cooled slightly.

title: malaysian fried beef bundles
directions: In food processor fitted with steel blade, combine onion, chili peppers, garlic and ginger.
Process until almost smooth. Set aside.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce and place in bottom of bowl.
Add each layer as listed.
Be sure mayonnaise covers all vegetables, sealing them in bowl.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix when ready to eat or dip as is.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and place in bottom of long baking dish.
Cover with pizza or spaghetti sauce, then add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in casserole and layer remaining ingredients in order given, except bacon.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Simmer 20 minutes. Add in three cups half & half cream. Simmer 10 minutes. Thicken.

title: butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except the sprinkles. Roll as thin as possible.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat together.
Serve on buns or as sauce for hot dogs.

title: lemon cranberry loaves
directions: Stir together cranberries, nuts and sugar in bowl; set aside. Combine cake mix, cream cheese and milk in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating an additional 2 minutes.
Fold in cranberry mixture.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. May be made ahead or frozen for later use. Remove from freezer about 3 hours before serving and place in refrigerator.

title: glaze for ham steak
directions: Boil ingredients (syrup, mustard and butter) in heavy saucepan until reduced about 1/3, about 3 minutes.
Broil ham in sauce until hot or about 1 minute.
Turn.
Spread with glaze and broil until other side is hot.
Cut and serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika after baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili cheese puff
directions: Line
a
12-inch
Dutch
oven
with
foil
and	grease. Sprinkle chilies and cheese evenly in oven.
Beat eggs, water, dried milk,
oregano,
basil
and
Bisquick until smooth.
Add bacon
and onions.	Pour into oven and bake 45 minutes with 10 coals on top and 6 coals on the bottom.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift together in a large blow:
Flour, Sugar, Baking Soda, Salt and Cinnamon, mix well.
Add Diced Bananas, Butter Flavored Oil. Beat 3 Eggs well and add to bowl.
Stir in gently Crushed Pineapple, Chopped Nuts and 1/2 tsp.
Vanilla.
Bake in a greased and Floured Bundt Pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well, until light.
Add sugar, flour, buttermilk and butter.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 300° until golden brown.
It will take about 1 hour.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix 3 egg yolks, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites and add cream of tartar.
When whites become stiff, add sugar.
Put on top of pie and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: banana chocolate bread(low fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: sock-it-to-me salmon patties
directions: In large mixing bowl, thoroughly beat eggs.
Stir in onion, croutons and salmon.
Stir well to blend.
Divide mixture into 4 rounded patties.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown patties on both sides.
Heat mushroom soup in small saucepan.
Add peas and butter; heat until butter melts, stirring to blend.
To serve, place patties on platter; spoon soup mixture over patties.
Makes 4 servings.

title: versatile barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan, cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sandwiches
directions: Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: saffron tea bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture with milk.
Stir in lemon juice and rind.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: white house croissants
directions: Place croissant halves, cut side up, on microwaveproof plate. Layer turkey, ham and cheese on each half.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on 80 for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Pour hot sauce over top.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening. Add sugar and cream well.
Add vanilla. Add eggs; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal. Add chips, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Put all other ingredients in medium bowl and mix.
Pour slowly into dry ingredients bowl and stir (do not mix).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vinegar cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, bell pepper, carrots and onion.
Boil vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard, pepper and salt for 5 minutes.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
If you keep it covered, it will keep for several days.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and butter, mixing until blended.
Add combined sugar, flour and spices; mix well.
Blend in eggs and milk.
Pour into crust.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cherries, then sprinkle cake mix on top and then the nuts.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine in blender.
Mixture will be thin but it thickens as it cools.
Store in fridge.
One cup equals 1 can of condensed milk.

title: microwave pecan or cashew brittle
directions: In greased 2-quart glass measure, cook sugar, corn syrup and salt on High for 2 to 3 minutes, until boiling.
Cook 4 minutes. Stir in nuts, butter, vanilla and cinnamon.
Cook 2 minutes. Immediately, stir in baking soda until light and foamy.
Quickly, pour onto greased cookie sheet; spread.
Cool; break into pieces. Makes 1 pound.

title: saffron rice(recipe from the club meeting's herbal luncheon)
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add rice and spices.
Reduce heat to lowest possible setting, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until done.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix ingredients well; refrigerate and use when hungry for good Mexican food or just to eat with chips.

title: easy lemon cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into little balls.
Press down.
Coat with powdered sugar.
Do not add any water or milk.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Coat baking dish with margarine.
Save leftover margarine to add to other ingredients.
Sprinkle half of the poultry stuffing on the bottom of the dish.
Mix together all other ingredients. Add in remaining melted margarine.
Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle remaining poultry dressing over the top.

title: hawaiian banana bread(heritage:  pacific coast)
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°. Cream the butter and sugar. Mix in the bananas, then add the eggs.
Sift the flour with the salt and baking powder.
Mix into banana mix, just enough to combine.
Do not overmix.
Fold in the nuts and pour into a buttered loaf pan. Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Stir together thoroughly the first three ingredients and 3/4 teaspoon of salt.
Make a well in the center.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together; mix all together.
Add chopped nuts; bake 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan, or use two 8-inch layer pans and bake until done (test with toothpick).
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix vegetables and pour 1/4 cup of salt over them; let sit for 2 hours.
Drain and set aside.
Bring the sugar, vinegar and seeds to a boil.
Add vegetables and boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: fruit tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add sugar, then other ingredients.
Serves 10.

title: homemade taco seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Seal and shake until evenly blended. This salt-free mix can be stored in an airtight container.
Makes 21 teaspoons (about 1/2 cup).

title: dilly macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain well and cool. Combine the next 4 ingredients.
Blend together remaining ingredients, then toss lightly together.
Cover and chill well. Serves 6.

title: darla's taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing mix and pour into a 2-quart long Pyrex dish (13 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch).
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Spread Ro-Tel tomatoes, green onions and jalapeno peppers in layers over first layer.
Just before serving, spread chopped fresh tomatoes and grated Cheddar cheese over other layers.
Serve as a dip with tortilla chips or Tostitos chips or serve over shredded lettuce as a salad with tortilla or Tostitos chips.

title: sherry and the devil
directions: Coat chicken completely with the mustard and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add the parsley to the bread crumbs and coat the chicken with this mixture.
Fry the chicken in 3 tablespoons of butter and oil mixture on each side until brown. Drain most of the oil off and reduce heat.
Pour sherry over the chicken and remove chicken to a serving platter.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to the sherry in the pan, scraping the drippings until well blended.
Pour over the chicken.
Serves six.

title: mother's christmas cranberry salad
directions: Make jello according to directions on boxes, using only 4 cups water.
Jell slightly.
Clean cranberries and chop in food processor.
Put sugar on cranberries and let set until jello is slightly jelled.
Add cranberries, celery and nuts to jello.
Let jell until firm.
When firm, mix 1/4 cup sugar in 8 ounces sour cream and spread over top.
Garnish with a few orange slices or cherries or canned whole cranberries.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: curried fruit
directions: Cut up fruit and place in Pyrex dish.
Drain fruit and save all juices.
Mix brown sugar and butter; add curry powder and 2 tablespoons of the juice from fruits. Drizzle over fruit in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, drizzling the casserole twice more with the juice mixtures.

title: popcorn snowman
directions: Accessories/Features:
Colored paper or yarn, gumdrops, raisins and chocolate chips.

title: cherry pineapple jello delight
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add can of cherry pie filling.
Mix and refrigerate until firm.

title: pasta fagoli
directions: Brown beef in large stew pot.
Drain.
Add onion, carrot, celery and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta.
Simmer 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In separate pan, put water on to boil.
Cook pasta 10 minutes.
Drain and add noodles to the soup, cook together 5 or more minutes to let the flavor blend into the pasta.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook your ground beef, onion and bell pepper together.
Grate both cheeses together in bowl.
