Drain excess grease and mix in tomatoes and seasoning mix.
Grease casserole dish with butter. Layer the bottom of the dish with chips, layer of meat sauce, then cheese until you have used all ingredients.
Put in oven at 325° until cheese melts.
Top with sour cream and picante sauce.
Very Good.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: angel muffins
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine with biscuit mix and sour cream. Spray muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour mix into muffin pan. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pineapple chicken breasts
directions: Drain pineapple.
Skin the split chicken breasts.
Pour pineapple juice 1/4-inch deep in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix salt, paprika, and flour.
Put on chicken breasts.
Put pineapple on chicken breasts.
Put pineapple juice on part of breasts not covered with pineapple.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.
Do not cover.
Baste.
If necessary, add more liquid.
Remove chicken from pan and keep in a warm place.
Put juice in Teflon skillet and make chicken gravy from flour mixture.
No fat.
No cholesterol. Delicious!

title: easy potato pancakes(makes 24 servings)
directions: Cut potatoes and onion in chunks.
Place in processor with eggs and process until pureed, about 20 to 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients.
Process a few seconds longer to blend for smooth mixture.
Pour oil in skillet to a depth of 1/8-inch.
When hot, drop potato mixture by large tablespoons to form pancakes. Brown well on each side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cantonese chicken wings
directions: Line 17 x 11-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Mix sauce ingredients and spread over chicken.
Marinate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mini burgers
directions: Mix
ground beef, soup mix and mayo in bowl.
Split pan of rolls
open.
Pat
of raw meat mix on each package of rolls. Top
with pickles and cheese.
Put roll back together. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and jar of salsa; put into a bowl. Sprinkle onion over cheese mixture.
Put shredded lettuce over onion.
Put a layer of diced tomatoes over lettuce; top with shredded cheese.
Chill 2 hours.

title: corn dogs
directions: In a bowl, combine cornmeal, flour and egg; mix well.
Stir in milk to make a thick batter.
Heat oil to 375 degrees.
Place a wooden stick through the hot dog, make sure it is firmly in place.
Dip hot dog in batter and fry until golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
As a substitute for self-rising flour, place 1 tsp. baking powder and 1/4 tsp. salt in a measuring cup.
Add enough all-purpose flour to equal 3/4 cup.

title: fantastic fruit dip
directions: Blend the first four ingredients well.
Thin mixture to desired consistency with pineapple juice.
Serve with apples, pineapple, bananas or any fresh fruit tray.

title: beef jerky(dehydrator recipe)
directions: Marinate in sauce above for 10 minutes.
Lay out separately in dehydrator and leave until fully dried, approximately 12 to 14 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cut strawberries into slices (save a few to slice on top). Mix together milk, pudding, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell (already baked).
Slice strawberries on top and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onions in saucepan.
Cook in water over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Drain in a colander.
Mash and add other ingredients (except cheese).
Place in greased 2-quart dish and cover top with the grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes and serve.

title: jelly roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom and sides of jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Line bottom of pan with greased aluminum foil or wax paper.

title: crockpot dressing
directions: Melt butter, and saute onions and celery.
Pour over croutons.
Add mushrooms and seasonings.
Pour broth over to moisten.
Add eggs and beat together. Cook in greased crockpot on high for 45 minutes.
Then cook on low 4-8 hours. Serves 6-8.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add cream (or milk).
Blend well.
Turn out on floured board and knead several times.
Divide into 6 or 8 parts.
Roll each part very thin.
On one half of each piece, place thick applesauce.
Fold over and seal with fork.
Bake or fry in well-greased skillet until golden on both sides.
Sprinkle sugar on pies.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add chicken.
When water boils again, add veggies and bouillon cubes; bring to boil again.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with noodles or rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs into sugar, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add with oil and sugar mixture.
Add carrots and nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a well greased pan.

title: pork speidies
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat in large bowl.
Mix with pork cubes.
Marinate overnight or more.
Place meat on skewers and barbecue until done.
This is a regional recipe from Upstate, NY.

title: taco salad
directions: Hints:
Drain meat well and chill before adding at the last minute to salad.
Chill beans separately.
Make salad dressing a day or several hours ahead and chill well.

title: easy strawberry jam
directions: Defrost strawberries and add the sugar and fruit pectin in a large saucepan over medium heat. Simmer for several hours.
Pour into jam jars (6 to 8) or any size jars available. Seal. Refrigerate if not sealed.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets; save water.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved beet liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add beets and heat through.
Serves 4.
These are yummy!

title: apple coleslaw
directions: Clean and shred cabbage. Core apple and cut into chunks with skin on. Peel and slice banana. Clean grapes and cut in half. Combine together until mixed thoroughly. Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and dash of salt together until creamy and sugar is dissolved. Pour over slaw and mix well. Let stand for one hour.

title: michael's baked chicken rolls and rice
directions: Cut chicken breasts into fillets (long and thin).
Marinate fillets in Italian dressing for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°. Make rice and place in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Place chicken on flat surface.
Put chopped vegetables and 2 slices of Swiss cheese on fillets.
Roll up tightly and pin with toothpick.
Dip rolls in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until brown.
Place on rice.
top with slice of tomato on each roll.
Bake for 1/2 hour, until done.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Boil sugar and syrup for 1 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Melt chips and pour over top.
Spread and cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour.
Spread over pineapple.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Spread over pineapple and flour mixture.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cucumbers
directions: Take cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let drain all day.
Then, squeeze out juice.
When ready to serve, put in 1 tablespoon sour cream, 1 or more teaspoons of vinegar and pepper to taste.

title: broiled wild duck with oranges in syrup
directions: Ducks are preferably hung, undrawn for 5 to 7 days and then dry plucked.
Some people prefer not to age the birds.

title: spinach loaf
directions: Stir together and pour into a greased loaf pan or baking dish. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes and serve with sauce.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add enough water to make a stiff dough.
Makes about 25 pies.

title: pastel delights
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Add egg, vanilla or almond extract.
Fold in flour with baking powder and salt. Blend to make stiff dough.
Divide dough in 1/2; leave 1 half plain and divide remaining dough in thirds.
Tint 1/3 green, one pink
and one yellow with a few drops of coloring.
Roll out 1/2 the plain dough to a 10 x 6-inch rectangle on a lightly floured board.
Shape 1/2 the pink dough into a 10-inch long rope.
Do the same with 1/2 the green and yellow dough.
Place each color rope on the long side of rectangle.

title: spike steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Crack peppercorns coarsely and mince garlic.
Press peppercorns and garlic into both sides of steak; let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Make a thick paste of salt and water.
Cover top side of steak with half the mixture. If cooking over coals, cover salt side with a wet cloth or paper towel and place salt side down on grill.
(Cloth or paper towel holds salt in place; will char as steak cooks but will not affect taste.)
Cover the top with remaining salt mix and another piece of towel.
If broiling, put salt side up, 3 inches from heat.
Put salt on other side of steak when turned.
Cook 15 minutes on each side for rare, 25 minutes for medium rare.
Remove salt before eating.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To prepare a cup of tea, take 5 to 6 teaspoons of mixture for large cup or 3 teaspoons for small cup.
Mix with hot water and serve.
Store dry mixture in airtight container.

title: party chicken
directions: Lay dried beef in casserole dish.
Wrap each breast with a small piece of bacon.
Lay chicken on top of dried beef.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup and sour cream, spoon over chicken.
Bake at 275 degrees for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: candy canes
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, confectioners sugar, egg, almond extract and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Divide the dough in half and blend food coloring into one half.
For each candy cane, shape 1 teaspoon of dough from each half into a 4-inch rope by rolling dough back and forth on a floured board.
Place ropes side by side and press together lightly.
Twist and curve top to form handle of cane.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix candy and granulated sugar and remove from baking sheet.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix thoroughly.
Add hot water to form a dough.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Form 12 balls from dough.
Roll balls into 6-inch round tortillas.
Cook tortillas on hot griddle (medium heat) until blisters form.
Turn tortilla over and cook opposite side for five seconds.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in the order listed.
Mix the mayo and sugar and spread on top.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.

title: easy frozen strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into crust. Freeze.

title: coconut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk; stir until moistened.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Freezes well.

title: super easy potato soup
directions: This is a rich and satisfying chicken soup. To make it heartier, add carrots or other suitable vegetables.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat ingredients to
mix well. Pour custard into 6 to 8 baking dishes. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place dishes in cake pan.
Pour water around custard dishes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted into the custard comes out clean.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, mustard and pepper. Stir in macaroni.
Combine margarine and bread crumbs in a bowl. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: cobbler
directions: Place either fresh or canned fruit in the bottom of a baking dish.
Add the sugar and water.
(Syrup from the canned fruit may be substituted for the water if desired).
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Cut in the shortening and add the milk.
Mix lightly and spread dough over the fruit in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in pie filling and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pleasin' pea salad(serves 4)
directions: In medium bowl combine peas, celery, cheese, olives and onions.
In small bowl, blend remaining ingredients until smooth. Stir into pea mixture; mix well.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: glorified rice
directions: While rice is hot, add sugar and marshmallows.
Let stand 1 hour.
Fold in whipping cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: bonnie's butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 3 round layer pans, 8 x 1 1/2-inch.
In large mixer bowl, mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat 5 minutes on High speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour batter into pan(s).
Bake oblong pan 45 to 50 minutes, layers 30 to 35 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool cake.
Frost with frosting.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat until smooth. Add vanilla, then flour and salt. Beat until smooth. Add pecans. Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Do not brown. Let cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: emma's cookies
directions: Relatively no cooking or baking.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil fryer in about 1-inch of water.
Remove when done and tear into bite size pieces.
Cook spaghetti in the chicken broth. In a small saucepan, combine oleo, bell pepper, onion and celery. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, then add to spaghetti.
Add chicken, soup and cheese.

title: janice's chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts into cubes.
Add soups, Veg-All, cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and broth.
Pour into a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Melt margarine and pour over cracker crumbs.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine the pumpkin and the eggs.
Add the salt, spices and evaporated milk and mix well.
Divide mixture between the pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 50 minutes more or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool with freshly made whipped cream.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Pour into gallon freezer and finish filling with milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: quick bean dip
directions: Mix beans and salsa thoroughly.
Add more salsa to taste if needed.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve chilled.
Great for last minute dip.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Work Crisco into dry ingredients until the size of peas.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken aloha
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add all ingredients together and stir.
Add chicken last.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 375°. Uncover and bake 15 more minutes, or use pressure pan for 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Great to freeze for once a month cooking.

title: pimento and cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, and store in sealed container in refrigerator. Serve on crackers, sandwiches, celery, etc.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place 4 pounds of country style ribs in large pan.
Add enough water to cover; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook 1 hour. Remove ribs; drain.
Place, bone side down, in grill 3 inches from medium coals.
Cook about 30 minutes, turning frequently.
Prepare Orange Sauce.
Spoon sauce on ribs; cook for 5 minutes.
Turn; spoon sauce on ribs and cook 5 minutes longer, or until ribs are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: delicious snack
directions: Combine the oil, dill, dressing and garlic; pour over the crackers.
Mix well.
Let stand for 1 hour (2 hours is better). Keep in airtight container.

title: dilled okra
directions: Pack okra into hot pint jars with a pod of pepper, clove of garlic and head of dill or dill seed in each jar.
Make a brine of water, vinegar and salt; heat to boiling.
Pour over okra.
Close jars.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Start to count processing time as soon as hot jars are placed in actively boiling water.
Makes 6 pints.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding one at a time and pour into large greased Bundt pan. Bake approximately 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Cake is done as soon as toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: banana party bread
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
add
eggs,
one
at
a
time, beating well.
Mix	in bananas.
Measure and sift together dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture.
Coat nuts and fruit with flour and add to
other
mixture.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 large tube pan.

title: distretti red rice
directions: Brown roast in oil on all sides.
Remove roast.
Brown onions and celery.
Add seasonings to onions and celery.
Return meat to pan.
Put onions and celery on top.
Mash tomatoes.
Add tomatoes, juice, sauce and 2 cups hot water.
Meat should be covered in sauce.
Simmer until tender (2 hours or more).
You need two cups of sauce for rice.
Pour 1 cup sauce in skillet.
Add rice and brown, 5 minutes at least.
Stir until sauce is absorbed (browning is secret).
Add water to cover rice.
Boil, then simmer uncovered about an hour.
Continue to stir.
Cook until liquid is absorbed but still juicy.
Save some sauce to serve as gravy with roast and rice.

title: infallible rice(serves 6)
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine onion, rice and hot broth.
Bring to a boil on top of range.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese olive snack
directions: When at room temperature, mash the cheese with a fork or mixer.
Work in the flour.
Add the Worcestershire.
Pat out flat. Roll a small amount around each olive.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot ham
directions: Wash ham and pat dry with paper towel.
Dissolve sugar in Coca-Cola, heated.
Place ham in crock-pot.
Pour Coca-Cola mixture over ham.
Cook 5 hours on high.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until done; drain.
Put 1/2 in greased casserole, then add 1/2 can cream of chicken soup and 1/2 package of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cream cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies. In separate bowl, mix milk and pudding. In another bowl, mix cheese and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip to pudding, then mix in cream cheese. Start with cookie on bottom of Pyrex dish, then a layer of mix. Continue layering. End with cookie on top.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove mushroom stems and finely chop; set caps aside.
Combine chopped mushroom stems, cheese, parsley and Italian dressing in a bowl, stirring well. Spoon mixture evenly into reserved mushroom caps and place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: popcorn uglies
directions: Boil Karo, sugar and salt together 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Gradually pour over popped corn; toss until coated. Grease hands; shape into balls and insert wooden sticks.
(If popcorn mixture cools during shaping place over low heat.)
Makes 6 popcorn balls.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Combine
ground
beef,	celery	and onion; microwave on High for 5 minutes, stir once.
Combine remaining ingredients, except frozen
peas and chow mein noodles.
Microwave on High for	3 minutes, covered.
Lower power to 80% and microwave for 6
to 8 minutes.
Add frozen peas.	Sprinkle chow mein noodles over top of casserole.	Microwave 1 minute on High, uncovered.

title: jim wogan's t v 6 big board chimichangas
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet.
Pour in 1/2 jar of picante sauce. Wrap a portion of beef with a portion of shredded cheese in each tortilla.
Place filled tortillas (1-inch apart) on a lightly greased, shallow cookie sheet.
Lightly brush tops of filled tortillas with squeeze margarine or vegetable oil and place in oven.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, until slightly browned and crisp.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cream yolks.
Add sugar then butter.
Mix well and add 1/2 cup milk, then flour, then rest of milk.
Cook over medium-low heat until thick.
Add coconut.
Remove from stove and add vanilla.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook in covered casserole at 325° for 1 hour.
Add more water if it gets too dry.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water for 5 minutes.
Save 1/4 cup juice. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on a greased baking sheet about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry nut pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla, butter flavoring, food color, and strawberry extract to buttermilk.
Blend well and set aside.
Sift flour, salt, powder and soda together.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk mixture until color is evenly distributed.
Fold in strawberries and pecans.
Blend well.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Do not over-bake.
Remove from pan while still hot.
Brush on glaze with pastry brush, covering top and sides of cake.

title: cinnamon nut brunch loaf
directions: Combine brown sugar, nuts, butter and cinnamon; set aside. Spray 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with cooking spray.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Combine milk and water; stir in vinegar. Add flour mixture alternately with milk mixture to creamed mixture. Blend well after each addition.
Pour half the batter into prepared pan.
Top with brown sugar and nut mixture.
Spread with remaining batter.
Bake in 325° oven 45 to 50 minutes.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting butter. Place rice in large bowl and add scallions, green pepper and olives; cool.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade.
Cut hearts in quarters.
Combine artichoke marinade, curry powder and mayonnaise.
Add artichoke hearts to rice mixture.
Toss with dressing and chill.
Chicken can be added to make this a main course dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: doris' applesauce cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour with nuts and raisins.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Bake in a tube pan in a moderate 350° oven until done.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
During the last 20 minutes baking time, pour remainder (1/2 can) of tomato sauce over top and finish cooking. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with flour, shaking off excess. In a large nonstick pot, heat oil; add beef and saute until brown. Remove and place on a plate. Add onions and mushrooms to pot; saute for 6 minutes. Add garlic and saute, stirring for 1 minute. Pour off fat. Return beef to pot; stir in tomato paste and the broth. Add enough water to cover; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Skim off any foam. Add carrots, potatoes and green beans. Cover partially and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage on bottom of casserole dish, then add meat, more cabbage and layer of onion.
Pour tomato soup over top and cover tightly.
Add 1/4 c. water. Salt & pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add tomato soup; pour mixture into a baking pan.
Add green beans; mix all around top of hamburger.
Take mashed potatoes and make mounds (about 6) on top of meat mixture.
Add slice of American cheese on top of potatoes. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn
directions: Melt cream cheese, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add corn and peppers.
Stir well.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake until heated through.

title: microwave english muffin bread
directions: Mix together flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add milk plus water.
Mix well with mixer.
Add additional flour; beat. Divide into 2 greased pans that have been sprinkled with corn meal. Sprinkle top with corn meal.
Set in oven with pan of warm water to rise about 40 to 45 minutes.
Bake each loaf in microwave 6 1/2 minutes.
Rest 5 minutes and remove.
Can add fruit, nuts or herbs.

title: easy does it flounder
directions: Arrange fillets in well greased shallow baking dish.
Spread soup over fillets.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: sweet and sour ham balls
directions: Mix together ham, pork, milk, eggs and corn flakes; shape into balls.
Brown in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes and drain.
Mix together brown sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar and dry mustard. Heat until well blended.
Pour over meat balls in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with salt and pepper; drain. Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs. Place in casserole dish at 325°; bake 30 minutes. Increase heat to 350°. Place buttered white bread crumbs on top and bake until browned.

title: german cold potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Cook onion in oil (very light). Add chicken broth, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Put over sliced potatoes (hot).
Mix occasionally; let stand overnight.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Put tomatoes in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes; peel off skins. Thinly slice tomatoes enough for 2 cups.
Mix all together, place in pie shell and dot with butter.
Place top crust, make steam holes in top crust and flute the edges.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: paradise salad
directions: Mix jellos with hot water.
Let jello begin to jell.
Add 1 large package cream cheese, softened.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Congeal.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and warm just enough to melt butter. Add nuts and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then lower temperature to 325°.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: popsicles
directions: Stir and add 2 cups cold water.
Pour into ice cube trays or frozen pop molds.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out.
Cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° until slightly brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: *You can use the chicken tender strips already cut.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Wash and cap hot peppers, leaving in seeds.
Chop fine in food processor. Combine all ingredients except flour and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Mix 1 cup flour and 1 cup water to make a runny paste.
Pour into hot pepper mixture.
Bring that to a boil.
Let mixture boil 10 minutes while stirring constantly. Put in jars and they will seal themselves.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients and set aside.
Heat milk, butter and marshmallows until melted.
Mix rest and cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Put in pie crust.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have cheese and sausage at room temperature. Mix cheese, sausage and Bisquick together. Make walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 15 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: apple or peach cobbler
directions: Line
pan
with
fruit	and
sprinkle
with
nutmeg and cinnamon.
If
using peaches, add a teaspoon of vanilla.
Make batter by mixing butter, sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt in a
bowl. Spread over fruit.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water.
Pour over batter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan patties
directions: Mix well and drop in small amounts on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until done.

title: granny creekmore's tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soups, onion and Tater Tots together.
Pour into casserole dish and top with slices of cheese. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Add salt and baking powder to three cups of the flour. Add to creamed mixture one egg at a time with one cup of the flour mixture each time. Add vanilla. Last, mix fruit and nuts with remaining cup of flour and add to batter. Spray bundt pan with pam. Preheat oven 250°. Bake 2 1/2 hr.
Cool in pan for 20 min.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add uncooked rice.
Remove fat and skin from chicken; arrange pieces on top of rice.
Mix soups, dry soup mix, water and pepper.
Pour mixture over rice and chicken. Bake uncovered for 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add cream of chicken soup, potatoes and sour cream.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add topping: Put on Cheddar cheese; on top of cheese, spread corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except vanilla wafers.
Line pan bottom and sides with vanilla wafers.
Place mixture in pan and top with more vanilla wafers.
Add Cool Whip and set in refrigerator about 2 hours.

title: savory dried lima beans
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Cover with cold water; let stand for awhile or overnight.
Drain; put into a pan.
Add 3 cups water, tomatoes, green peppers, onion and syrup.
Mix paprika, salt and mustard; stir into mixture.
Cook until almost tender. Render bacon; add and cook until beans are done.
Add more water as needed.
May also be baked in the oven.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up tomatoes in cubes.
Shred lettuce.
Crush chips in bag. Mix lettuce, tomatoes and chips; set aside.

title: cheesy asparagus casserole
directions: Combine butter and flour in a small saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Gradually stir milk into flour mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese and salt, stirring until cheese melts.

title: weight watcher's salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits.
Mix cottage cheese and dry Jell-O. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add chopped minced fruits.
Serve.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Beat well.
Add flour, milk, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Mix well.
Beat egg yolks and add to other ingredients.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly until thick.
Add butter and pour into baked pastry shell.
Put meringue on top, using 2 egg whites. Brown in hot oven.

title: muffalata
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Split bun in half.
Layer one half with meats, then spread with olive mixture. Top with cheese.
Put top on bun; cut in half and enjoy.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Pour in bottom of pie crust.
Layer sliced bananas and then pineapple. Put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken, cool, debone and set aside.
With a little oleo on both sides of tortillas, fry over medium heat until softened. Set aside.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add soup, most of cheese and sour cream; mix well.
Set aside one-fourth of sauce.
Add chicken to remainder of sauce.
Put chicken mixture in middle of tortilla; roll.
Place in baking pan with seam side down.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining grated cheese over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until hot.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Use oblong cake pan.
Mix soft cream cheese, vanilla pudding and two cups milk.
Put on top of cooled cake.

title: eggplant and tomato casserole
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons dripping in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute green pepper and onion in drippings until tender. Add eggplant and tomatoes.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spoon eggplant mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole and top with bacon. Sprinkle cheese over casserole; top with breadcrumbs.
Bake casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: raspberry angel cake
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1
cups
boiling water; add 2 cups cold water and stir
over ice water until thickened.
Blend in Cool Whip; add fruit.
Pour
in
pan
and let set (Bundt pan). Mix raspberry juice with
2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch over heat until clear and thick.
Drizzle over cake before serving.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: molded crab salad
directions: Heat tomato soup with 1/2 can water. Dissolve jello in soup. Add next 4 ingredients.
Beat cream cheese and add to soup mixture.
Fold in crabmeat.
Chill in mold until set.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Toss candy, dates, and nuts in 1/2 cup of the flour.
Sift remaining flour and soda.
Add alternately with the milk to the batter. Stir in coconut and candy mixture.
Grease a tube pan and line bottom with waxed paper.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until toothpick inserted in the cake comes out clean.
Remove from oven and glaze.

title: dirt cup or worm farm(kids recipe)
directions: Follow directions on both chocolate and vanilla pudding boxes. Keep puddings in separate bowls.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Pour
into pans.
Bake in center of oven until top is golden brown and splits slightly, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: danish pork chops
directions: Topping:
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and add milk slowly.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add eggs.
Cook over low heat, beating well, until consistency of mashed potatoes.
Add onion, cheese, salt and pepper; mix.

title: rainbow jello(12 layer jello)
directions: Dissolve 1 pkg. of purple jello in one cup boiling water. Take 1/2 cup of the hot water dissolved jello and add 1/3 cup sour cream (at room temperature), then add 2 Tbsp. cold water. Pour this into a 9x13 clear glass pan. Break any bubbles and put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour to an hour. After this is set, add 1/2 cup cold water to the remaining jello. Pour on top of the first layer. Let set.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Cook like custard. Let cool before serving. Use any fruit to dip or pour sauce over fruit.

title: vanilla sugar
directions: Add the vanilla to the confectioners sugar.
Mix well and press through a sieve.
Prepare before baking cookies so it will have time to dry.

title: colonial pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, salt, spices and molasses; mix well.
Add eggs and milk; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Add the rest of the ingredients. This recipe makes about 12 fruit pies, depending on the thickness of crust.

title: brown beef stew and biscuits
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste. Flour heavily and brown with 4 tablespoons extra flour.
Drain off excess fat.
Return meat to pot.
Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Add vegetables to pot.
Add 3 to 4 cups water.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until meat is tender. Top with biscuits and let brown uncovered for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Arrange dough in 2 long loaves about 2-inches high on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Cut into slices. Separate.
Bake for an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: honey bee ambrosia(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Pare oranges.
Cut crosswise into thin slices and place in serving bowl.
Peel banana.
Cut thin slices into bowl with oranges; toss fruit.
Blend orange juice, honey and lemon juice; pour over fruits.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add soda and spices to flour.
Add buttermilk.
Beat in berries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers in 8 or 9-inch pans.

title: low-fat oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix margarine, applesauce and sugars until smooth.
Add the egg substitute and vanilla and mix.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually add to the sugar mixture.
Add the oatmeal and raisins and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until light (not frothy).
Slowly add remaining ingredients.
(Can be stored in refrigerator for 3 days; add more soda to make cakes rise.)
Fry on hot griddle.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Dissolve soda in applesauce, then add to fruit mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add slowly and beat.
Add nuts, raisins and mixed fruits.
Bake in large tube pan on 250° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Cut up to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus bisque
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter;
set aside.
Make a roux by melting butter in
stockpot and adding flour gradually while stirring constantly.
Make sure mixture doesn't burn.
Add 1 quart milk slowly to roux mixture, stirring constantly.
When combined and thickened, add remaining milk, chicken stock and onion.
Add bay leaf, pepper and salt.
Add asparagus and simmer for 1 hour. Makes 1 gallon.

title: batter bread
directions: Sift together meal, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add boiling water, stirring to prevent lumps.
Beat eggs.
Add milk to them and add to meal mixture.
Pour into baking dish in which shortening has been melted.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 40 minutes.
After removing from the oven, run knife around edge of baking dish.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Add vinegar and salt.
Mix well and place in glass quart jar with tight lid.
This will last in the refrigerator a month.
The longer it sets the better it gets.
The peppers to use depends on how hot you want it.

title: super chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish; put rice, bouillon, mushroom and/or vegetables.
Stir.
Put chicken on top.
Put soup mix on top or mix with rice.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa well.
Add milk and butter, but do not stir.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Stir and add vanilla and nuts.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Freezes well too.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed.	Mix all and serve.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugars, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flours, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Fold in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown and springs back when touched, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting:

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt the margarine and unsweetened chocolate together.
Cream other ingredients together. Combine melted chocolate and margarine and mixture of eggs, 1 tablespoon of canned milk and sugar.
Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ginny niemann's swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately flour and buttermilk.
Add rolled oats and 1 cup chopped dates.
Bake in moderate oven, approximately 35 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice pickles; chop the onions and mangos, then add the salt and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Add the sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery or mustard seed.
Cook through and can.

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, white sugar, brown sugar, margarine and vanilla with mixer until smooth. Add by hand the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add oatmeal and chocolate morsels.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Grown meat in skillet and drain fat.
Add 1/2 package of burrito seasoning and 1/4 cup water.
Heat.
Melt just enough margarine to cover bottom of electric skillet.
Spoon meat mixture into tortillas and add 1 slice of cheese to each tortilla.
Fold each one in half.
Place in electric skillet and brown.
Turn once.
Garnish each quesadilla with chopped tomato, sour cream, guacamole and picante sauce.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine candy bars and 1/2 cup melted butter in a saucepan; place over low heat until candy bars are melted, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Put dry jello with Cool Whip. Do not add water with jello. Drain oranges and pineapple and add. Add cottage cheese and nuts. Chill and serve.

title: marinated oysterettes
directions: Spread crackers on cookie sheet.
Mix oil, Ranch dressing and dill weed.
Pour over crackers and mix well.
Put in airtight container.
Shake often to mix and let set overnight.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend warm cheese and margarine.
Mix in flour, salt and pepper.
Last, mix in Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonful; mark with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be stored in tin, frozen, thawed and then baked.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Soften margarine and mix with flour and nuts using pastry blender. Press into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Allow crust to cool.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Sprinkle jello on fruit cocktail.
Mix in all other ingredients.

title: chocolate chip crime cake
directions: Bake as directed on package in 8-inch round pans.
Spread 1/3 of whipped topping between layers. Top with chocolate sauce and remaining topping.

title: summer shish kebabs
directions: You will need six to eight 16-inch skewers.

title: company pepper beef
directions: Press pepper firmly in all sides of the brisket.
Combine soy sauce, vinegar, catsup, paprika and garlic.
Put meat in dish and pour marinade over it.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or until fork-tender.
Slice thinly.

title: diabetic spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until plump.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well by hand.
Grease and flour tube pan. Pour in batter and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate covered party mix
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together.
Melt the chocolate in the microwave.
Mix chocolate and the cereal mixture.
Add the M&M's.
Spread on wax paper to harden.
Crumble into chunks and store.

title: raspberry tomato jelly
directions: Skin, sieve and chunk up tomatoes.
Add sugar and lemon juice. Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in raspberry jello. Fill jars and keep in refrigerator or freeze.

title: lime delight
directions: Mix thoroughly boiling water with lime jello.
Blend into jello mixture the remaining ingredients.
Chill for about 2 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Top leaves of spinach with mandarins, onion and pepper.
Serve with no-fat honey-Dijon dressing.
Top with croutons.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add and mix all ingredients in order.

title: cajun fried crawfish tails
directions: Mix eggs, milk, baking powder and vinegar.
Season tails and marinate in mixture for at least 1 hour.
Remove, dip each tail in flour and fry at 380° in grease until brown.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft but not brown.
Add ground meat, breaking up meat until cooked.
In a 2-quart buttered casserole dish, layer carrots and half the cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add meat mixture and press down slightly.
Add remaining cabbage to spaghetti sauce.
Add Worcestershire sauce and chives.
Pour sauce over top of casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until cabbage is soft and meat is cooked through.
Add cheese on top.
Bake another 5 to 8 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: s. o. s.
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Remove meat from pan and keep grease. Add flour to grease to make a thick gravy.
Add meat to gravy and use onion salt and garlic powder to taste.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container; cover and blend till smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Fold in sour cream and flavoring.
Mix in flour.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Simmer until all vegetables are tender.
(Beef broth can also be used.)
This is a good way to use up leftover vegetables.
Add enough water to make soup the thickness you want.

title: dad's pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, mace and salt together 3 times. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Makes 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Cook ground beef. Add onion, salt and pepper.
Spread chilies over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour egg mixture over meat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven until melted.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart baking dish and coat well.
Mix all remaining ingredients together until moistened.
Pour into dish and mix in margarine.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Brown the meat, mushrooms and onion in the butter or shortening.
Stir in flour and salt. Add mushroom liquid, water and the Heinz 57 sauce.
Stir well. Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream. Serve immediately over the noodles.

title: pork tenderloin with brandy
directions: Cut pork crosswise into six pieces.
Flatten each by covering with waxed paper and mashing with a saucepan bottom, mallet or cleaver until 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange medallions in one layer on bottom of a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with waxed paper.
Turning over and rearranging medallions midway, microwave on Medium-high (70%) 4 to 5 minutes; set aside.
Place apples in a two-cup glass measure.
Add margarine and onions. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High 3 minutes.
Remove apples with a slotted spoon; add to pork.
Add brandy, water and brown sugar to drippings in glass measure.
Do not cover. Microwave on High 4 minutes, or until sauce is slightly reduced. Arrange pork and apples on serving plates. Spoon sauce over pork.

title: microwave pie
directions: Combine all except the egg whites and vanilla.
Microwave 5 minutes on High, then stir.
Microwave 5 more minutes, stirring once.
Remove; if not thickened, microwave 2 to 3 more minutes. Add butter (as desired) and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set and serve.

title: fluffy duffy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and press into 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° (glass pan 10 minutes; metal pan 15 minutes).
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over crust.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over first
mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and grate chocolate bar over top.

title: apple cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a small bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Set aside.
Separate and layer biscuits on a cookie sheet.
Flatten with hands or a rolling pin.
Peel, core and chop apples.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over biscuits.
Top with chopped apples.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Drizzle caramel topping over top.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans and place in large pot with water and seasoning meat and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add garlic, celery, onion, bell pepper and continue cooking an additional 1/2 hour or until tender.
Add cayenne pepper and salt to taste.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 10.

title: cheese balls
directions: Put all cheeses and other ingredients together.
Beat at medium speed until fluffy.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Form in two balls and roll in parsley flakes and nuts.

title: root beer float cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cake mix (dry), root beer, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool.
Serve with Root Beer Cream.
Sprinkle with crushed root beer hard candies, if desired.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cut Velveeta into pieces.
Put all ingredients into Pyrex or Corning Ware covered casserole.
Heat slowly in oven or on Low in microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir often while heating.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Rinse rice in strainer under cold water.
Combine with chicken stock and water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes.
Rice should not be too soft. Drain.
Combine rice with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Let stand 2 hours.
Serve at room temperature.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Stir with mixer eggs, mashed bananas, flour, soda and nuts (optional). Mix together.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean and cut spinach.
In a large bowl mix all ingredients together.
Serve with Italian dressing.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine the corn meal and salt; bread the tomatoes.
In a frypan, cook the
cooking
oil
hot and fry the tomatoes.
A delicious breakfast treat served hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili
directions: Combine beef and onion in a Dutch oven.
Cook until beef is browned, stirring frequently to crumble meat.
Drain off all drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: good easy cake
directions: Let strawberries thaw completely.
Make cake as directed. Cool.
Make holes in cake with a knife; pour sweet condensed milk on top of cake.
Spread strawberries over next; top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: mock champagne
directions: Combine pineapple juice, apple juice, lemonade concentrate and sugar.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Store in freezer overnight or longer.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer 3 or 4 hours before serving so juice becomes mushy.
Break up mixture and place in a large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale; do not add any ice.
Yields 40 (6 ounce) servings.

title: orange roughy vera cruz
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 7 minutes or until tender.
Add bell pepper and tomatoes.
Cook over medium-high heat 3 minutes.
Add fish. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Cover.
Reduce and let simmer 5 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, one hour at 325°.

title: cloud 9
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail and pour cocktail into a medium size mixing bowl.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.
Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: green bean-tomato bake
directions: Combine green beans and tomatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook bacon and onion.
Add onions to casserole along with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease 12 (3-inch) muffin pan cups.
Preheat oven to 400°. Measure flour, sugar, pecans, oats, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl.
Stir together.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly with a fork; stir in zucchini and oil.
Stir egg mixture all at once into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Remove muffins from pans. Serve warm or cool.

title: pineapple up-side down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
Stir together brown sugar and butter in bottom of a 10 inch iron skillet.
Arrange 7 pineapple slices in syrup mixture.
Half rest of slices and arrange around sides of the skillet.
Keep skillet warm while preparing cake mix according to directions on package.
Spread on top of pineapple. Bake at 350 degrees for about 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Let stand 5 minutes before turning out onto platter.

title: broiled chicken breasts(marguerite huey's)
directions: Line a big pan with foil.
Place breasts, fat side down, on foil. Salt and pepper to taste.
Dot each breast with butter (or oleo).
Put lemon juice into a 2/3 measuring cup.
Finish filling with cold water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Before serving, pour the broth into small pan and thicken with cornstarch.
Stir in the almonds and pour the gravy over the chicken which has been turned over. Keep warm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to directions on box.
Beat cream cheese.
Blend in 1/2 Cool Whip.
Line pan (bottom and sides) with wafers and bananas.
Add 1/2 pudding mix on top.
Add another layer of bananas and wafers.
Spoon in rest of pudding mix.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed wafers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Knead in flour until dough is semi-firm.

title: happiness is homemade
directions: Mix well and serve daily.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Drain off excess water. Add everything else except Ritz crackers.
Mix all together really good.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and asparagus roll-ups
directions: Drain asparagus and place on a paper towel.
Pat dry.
Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on each slice of boiled ham.
Place an asparagus spear on edge, lengthwise of each.
Roll up tightly; wrap in foil.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice, 1/2 to 3/4 inch in length.
Secure each with a toothpick.

title: jalapeno lime chicken
directions: Take the chicken and brown them on one side in a skillet.
Add the jalapenos and lime juice.
Then brown the other side in the juice.
When the chicken is fully cooked, put 2 tablespoons of the juice and jalapenos on top of each breast.
Cover with 2 slices of cheese.
Reduce heat and cover.
When the cheese melts, the chicken is ready to serve.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs with a fork to blend.
Add oil and both sugars. Continue mixing by hand until thick.
Spoon in zucchini.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients, chips and nuts.
Add dry mixture to liquid.
Stir gently until moist.
Fill 2 loaf pans 3/4 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Food process garlic and parsley. Add beans and process slightly. Add salsa and process just to mix.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well.
It will make 8 cakes.
They are great broiled or fried.
I use food processor and chopper to mash crackers and green peppers.
Mix all ingredients by hand.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and syrup, creaming well.
Add salt to the eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans to first mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together; set aside. Combine white sugar, brown sugar, eggs, butter (melted) and peanut butter.
Mix in flour mixture and milk, alternating.
Mix with beater for about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: cinnamon crisp snack mix
directions: Break Cinnamon Crisp into bite-size pieces.
Spread Cinnamon Crisp pieces, raisins, nuts and sunflower seeds on large greased jelly roll pan, about 15 x 10-inch.
In small saucepan, melt oleo with honey.
Drizzle over graham mixture.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan.
Loosen mixture with metal spatula.
Store in airtight jar or container.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Stir together rice and
sour
cream.
Spoon
into 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with
cup
of the grated cheese. Mix chicken with sauce and pour over rice.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Top with corn
chips
and
bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls in greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Beat well with electric beater, spread over cooled crust. Top with 1/2 cup each of fresh vegetables (your choice). Examples:
tomatoes, mushrooms, cauliflower, radishes, onions, broccoli, etc., chopped fine.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese (your choice).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and cool first 2 ingredients.
Cream and add next 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sun tea
directions: Water must be hot (tap water).
Add tea bags and sugar.
Set out in sun or on countertop.
Serve over ice and add lemon.

title: nachos
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain off grease.
Stir in refried beans.
Pour in tomatoes and green chilies.
Stir and heat all together.
Spoon mixture on corn chips (Tostitos).
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Heat in microwave until cheese is melted.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until very light and fluffy.
Add
flavorings.
Add
eggs,
one	at a time, beating well
after
each
addition.
Mix baking powder with flour and add alternately
with	milk, beginning and ending with flour. Bake in a tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until done.

title: krispie cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cheese mixture.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Let dough stand in refrigerator overnight or until chilled.
Roll into small balls and flatten into small wafers with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.
May be doubled.

title: souper meat 'n potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (or microwave at Full power for 12 minutes, turning pie plate a half turn after 6 minutes of cooking time).
Spoon off fat.
Frost with mashed potatoes; top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more (or microwave 3 minutes more to melt cheese).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage rice bake
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch chunks (remove skin, if desired). Combine with all remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Cook cornstarch and cold water until it's thick and clear; put into meringue while hot and beat in.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve and enjoy.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons Crisco and add mixture to dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix by hand and add raisins.
Put into large (12-inch) round baking pan.
Bake for a total of 1 1/2 hours.
First 1/2 hour bake at 325°, then lower to 300° for remaining hour.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: fish balls with parsley sauce(makes 12 servings)
directions: Thaw haddock just enough to cut into chunks with a heavy knife.
Put through a food grinder twice, using a fine blade. Place in a large bowl.
Beat in cracker meal, salt, pepper and cream until mixture is smooth.
Moisten hands.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.

title: cherry chocolate cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder and soda. Set aside. In mixer bowl, beat together margarine and sugar on low speed until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until blended. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press down center of dough with thumb. Drain cherries, reserving juice. Place a cherry in the center of each cookie.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, salt and water until a small amount forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Take out 1/2 cup of this mixture and cook the rest until it forms a hard ball when tried in cold water.
Pour the 1/2 cup of syrup slowly over the beaten egg whites.
Beat constantly.
Continue beating.
Add the remains of the syrup.
Add nuts and vanilla; keep beating until mixture thickens and becomes heavy.

title: pita pockets
directions: Slice potatoes, tomatoes and eggs.
Drain tuna.
Cut tuna and beans into small pieces.
Combine.
Blend vinegar, oil, salad herbs and oregano.
Fill pita breads with tuna mixture.
Sprinkle with dressing.
Serve.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a mixer.
May be stored in refrigerator.
Use as a dip or on sandwiches.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot greased skillet; bake at 450° until brown.
This makes 3 skillets, 1/3 recipe makes 1 skillet.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour half of batter into hot greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet. Sprinkle cheese. Then pour remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bean sprout salad
directions: Blanche bean sprouts in boiling water for 2 minutes and drain thoroughly.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a large bowl, then add the drained sprouts.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Combine together with mixer on medium speed.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine the pumpkin, sugar, salt, and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk, and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell (have edges crimped high - filling is generous).
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside come out clean.
Cool.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake white cake mix according to directions.
Split layers to make 4 layer cake.
Ice heavily all layers, top and sides. Refrigerate overnight.

title: **orange slice cookies
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees (325 degrees for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9 inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over margarine.
Top evenly with coconut then Eagle Brand milk.
Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: yvonne's cookies
directions: Beat margarine until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients (except almonds); mix well.
You can knead this like a dough. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with a lightly floured fork.
Slide slivered almonds into the top of each cookie. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes to barely light gold.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: crunchy pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in oil, egg and vanilla.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Add dry into creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoon 2 inches apart.
Flatten with fork dipped in water. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Store in airtight container.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion; pour off fat. Blend in pizza sauce, garlic salt and oregano.
Put mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella.

title: crab scallop casserole
directions: Place snow crab (cut into small pieces) in casserole with scallops.
Cut garlic (small) and parsley (small).
Place in with other ingredients in casserole.
Squeeze 2 lemons into mixture and wine, if desired.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, place some bread crumbs on top of mixture and some oil sprinkled on top.
Bake in 400° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat the eggs and add to this mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until done, about 25 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion and the green pepper. Add garlic salt, oregano and pepper.
Add salt, celery salt and chili powder.
Add tomato sauce and all beans.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes before serving.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and sour cream; mix.
Add salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour; beat until smooth.
Spoon half of batter into tube pan.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water (110°) and sugar.
Set aside 10 minutes or until yeast becomes spongy.
(If this does not occur, start over with new yeast or bread will not rise.)

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix all together until crumbly.
Put in airtight container; keep in a cool place.
Use 1 1/2 cups mix and 2 to 3 tablespoons water for 1 pie crust.
Very quick and simple!

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in cocoa or powdered sugar.
Age 1 week before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball and roll in nuts. Chill at least 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle shredded Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread (cut in 1-inch squares) and put in greased baking dish.
Cut smoky links and put over bread.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over meat.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Pour over other ingredients and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean like custard.
Can be made the night before.

title: father's favorite fudge
directions: In large bowl cook all ingredients, except vanilla and nuts, in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add 3/4 cup nuts (optional).
Grease 6 x 6-inch pan. Pour into pan.
Freeze 10 minutes.

title: salmon and rice casserole
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients; layer heated items, rice and salmon in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; bake 10 minutes.
Stir and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: after dinner mints
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine with flavoring and enough food coloring to tint desired shade.
Add powdered sugar, gradually mixing well.
Roll into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Press into molds or press with thumb or crisscross with fork.

title: sho-nuff cajun slurp
directions: Heat fat or bacon drippings in heavy skillet.
Add flour to make roux.
Add other vegetables and cook until soft, about 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned oven pancake
directions: In bowl combine flour and half of milk.
Beat until smooth. Add eggs one at a time, beating.
Stir in rest of milk.
Set aside for a short time while preparing bacon.
Cut bacon into small strips or cubes.
Saute lightly in a skillet.
Distribute bacon bits in an ovenproof casserole and pour pancake batter over it.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until set and golden brown.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.
There are 35 calories per serving.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Make a custard using the juice from the pineapple, salt, sugar, flour, butter, and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Mash sweet potatoes in dish.
Add thickened custard to potatoes.
Make a meringue using left over egg whites.
Add sugar to taste.
Cook in oven until meringue darkens between 325-350°, depending on your oven.
Marshmallows can be used in place of egg whites.

title: lemon chicken on angel hair pasta
directions: Roll chicken breasts in flour.
Set aside.
Melt
butter in a large skillet.
Slowly pan-fry breasts in butter until crispy brown (about 15 minutes).
Pour wine and chicken broth into skillet with chicken. Add onions and mushrooms. Squeeze lemon juice over mixture. Add several lemon slices on top. Season to taste with Tony Chachere seasoning mix.
Simmer for 20 minutes until broth thickens.
Serve over cooked angel hair pasta.

title: angel cake
directions: Combine egg whites, baking powder and cream of tartar; beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar and flour.
Blend in flavorings.
Pour into medium size cake pan; place cake in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: european apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 10-inch tube pan.
In a separate bowl, combine apples, cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar.

title: apple dumplings with cream sauce
directions: Mix together.
Roll small portions of pastry to size of saucer.
Peel
and	chop
5 fresh apples.
Place 2 tablespoons apples, 2 teaspoons sugar, 1 teaspoon butter and a sprinkle of cinnamon on pastry.
Bring edges together and crimp.
Place in greased
baking
dish.
Bake
minutes at 375°.	Serve with Cream Sauce.

title: mary's banana cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 2 layers as directed on box.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll Pillsbury croissants out on a cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Mix other ingredients and spread over crust. Grate or break into small pieces the following veggies: carrots, broccoli, bell pepper and cauliflower.
Sprinkle these over mixture.
Grate Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle over veggies.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini and steam 5 minutes.
Chop afterwards into smaller pieces.
Mix in onion and carrots.
Combine soup and sour cream, stir in vegetable mixture.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and add to box of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix (or favorite brand).
Place 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of large casserole.
Add vegetables, then cover with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spamburgers
directions: Grind Spam, cheese and onion together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put mixture on hamburger rolls and broil until cheese bubbles or wrap in foil and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: angela pia
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until creamy mass results.
Add brandy and rum.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Whip cream until stiff enough to stand in firm, shiny peaks.
Add vanilla.

title: raw apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix apples and sugar together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together four, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Add to above mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 3 x 2 inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven-fried shark
directions: Wipe fillets with damp cloth.
Pour milk into small mixing bowl.
Add salt, pepper and basil.
Stir well.
Dip each fillet in seasoned milk then in bread crumbs.
Arrange in buttered shallow baking dish and pour melted butter on fish.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: best corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir with spoon until mixed well. Pour into preheated iron skillet.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberry or cherry topping.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices. Add to cream mixture alternately with the applesauce. Beat well and stir in nuts and raisins. Spread batter in a Pam sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in large bowl.
Add beans, tomato, pepper, onion and egg.
Mix together.
Pour into an oblong glass casserole.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, picante, pickles, etc., and spread over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: mixed vegetable medley
directions: Cook your fresh vegetables, done but firm. Combine soup, Cheez Whiz, milk and seasonings.
Pour over vegetables which were placed in a greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add browned bread crumbs and bake, uncovered, another 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces. Fry bacon until crisp. Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise together. Mix in large bowl the broccoli, cauliflower, onion, crumbled bacon and cheese. Add dressing; mix well. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: italian chicken rolls(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pound each chicken breast to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut cheese and Prosciutto slices into halves. Layer cheese and Prosciutto on chicken. Roll to enclose filling. Secure with toothpicks or kitchen twine. Mix paprika, bread crumbs, Parmesan, garlic salt, oregano and basil in a shallow dish. Dip chicken rolls into butter. Roll in crumb mixture to coat. Place rolls seam side down in a baking dish. Bake for 25 minutes or until chicken is done and golden brown.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onions. Mix with celery and soups. Add milk if more moisture is needed. Add mushrooms.
Add noodles and nuts just before placing in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato and banana puree
directions: Place the sweet potatoes in a medium-size saucepan and add water to cover.
Cook covered until very tender; drain.
Cut bananas into 1-inch pieces and puree in a food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Add the hot sweet potatoes, 4 tablespoons of the butter, the rum and brown sugar.
Process until smooth.
Add the nutmeg and salt to taste; process just to blend.
Keep warm. Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a small skillet.
Add the almonds and saute until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
Top each serving of the sweet potato puree with a generous amount of the toasted almonds.
Yields 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Keep refrigerated in closed container.
Will keep up to 1 month in refrigerator.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: spinach-avocado salad
directions: Toast sesame seed in ungreased shallow pan in a 350° oven, stirring occasionally, until golden, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef chiliquillas
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake tortillas until crisp, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Increase oven heat to 350°.
Brown meat in a frying pan; drain off any fat and add tomato paste, chilies and tomatoes, half the chopped onion and cayenne pepper.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer beef mixture, broken tortillas, remaining onion and cheese three times, in that order, in a 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Serve with lettuce,
tomato and salsa, if desired.
Good with refried beans and fresh corn-on-the-cob.
Serves 4.

title: cheese apples
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, put 2 thinly sliced zucchini squash or enough to make 1 1/2 to 2-inches deep in bottom of pan.
Salt to taste.
Slice enough onions to cover zucchini.
Slice enough fresh tomatoes to cover onions.
Sprinkle small package of Pepperidge Farm stuffing crumbs over tomatoes.
Drizzle 2/3 cup melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and flavoring. Add 1 cup self-rising flour, 1/2 cup milk, then 2 cups plain flour and rest of milk.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°. Use tube pan, greased and floured.

title: easter eggs
directions: In a large bowl, mix with your hands the cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and peanut butter or coconut.
Gradually add 10x sugar and continue mixing with hands.
Form eggs and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all except cheese.
Pour half of batter in greased frying pan, sprinkle cheese over all and add rest of batter.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare enchilada sauce mix.
Brown meat.
Place tortillas and meat in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over tortillas and meat.
Place cheese, onion and cilantro on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweep steak
directions: Place
meat in center of a large piece of aluminum foil in roasting
pan.
Combine onion soup mix and undiluted cream of mushroom
soup; pour mixture over meat and wrap loosely in foil. Bake
until
tender
at
350° for 3 hours.	You may add potatoes and carrots.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets and combine with thinly sliced onions, bacon, mushrooms and raisins.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and pour over vegetables; stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled and seasoned through.
Can set overnight.
Stir before serving.
Be aware that the longer the salad sets, it will reduce considerably in volume.
I usually double or triple the amounts when making the salad for the smorgasbords.

title: bread sticks
directions: Open buns; slice in half.
Dip top side in oleo.
Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with seasoning.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Makes 32.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Blend mayo, milk, eggs and cornstarch. Stir in meat.
Add cheese, onion, salt and pepper (to taste).
Mix well.
Pour into deep dish frozen pie crust.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Cook until thickened; cool.
Add whipped topping.
Add to fruit.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring to a boil rice, water and salt.
Lower heat and simmer 12 to 14 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to cooked rice in baking dish.
Bake until it comes to a boil, 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk and shortening.
Stir in nuts.
