Pour into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
While hot, cut into squares.
Invert each piece onto plate.
Spoon sauce over each and top with whipped cream.

title: microwave chocolate cake
directions: Grease microproof baking dish.
Line bottom with plastic wrap. In small, microproof bowl, combine cocoa and 1/3 cup water. Microwave on High 40 to 50 seconds.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oil, remaining 1/3 cup hot water, egg, vanilla and chocolate mixture. Beat until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto plate.
Peel off plastic wrap and cool.
Frost.

title: american flag cake
directions: At high speed, mix whipping cream until peaks.
Add sugar until stiff.
Spread cream over top and sides of cake (removed from pan and placed on serving board).
Mark 7 1/2 x 5-inch top corner of cake.
Place berries in even rows for stars.
Alternate rows of strawberries and bananas for stripes, overlapping fruit.
Chill until serving, up to 2 hours.
Great for 4th of July.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding apples and nuts last.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut as a pie.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon plus cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While still hot, poke holes 1-inch apart with fork.
Dribble top of cake with juice of 2 lemons and 2 cups powdered sugar mixed until smooth.

title: crab treat
directions: Stir butter and cheese; mix together well.
Add crab and garlic salt.
Cut English muffins apart.
Spread mixture on muffin halves.
Cut English muffin halves in fourths to make bite size treats.
Brown in oven at 350° for a few minutes.
Enjoy.

title: edible holiday centerpiece
directions: Combine margarine and marshmallows in top of double boiler. Put over hot water and heat until melted and well mixed.
If you do it over direct heat, keep heat low and stir and watch.
Add coloring and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over corn flakes or if pot is large, add corn flakes to warm mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to form a 9-inch wreath.
Shape with hands and spoon or put waxed paper into 10-inch tube pan and use this to shape wreath. Decorate with red cherries.
If you plan to eat it soon, use maraschino cherries.
If you want to keep it a week or so, use candied cherries or silver dragees.
Stand a red candle (3-inches in diameter) in wreath.

title: mayonnaise biscuit
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a fork and then take a tablespoon and fill a well-greased muffin pan that holds 6 drop muffins.
Preheat oven; cook at 450°.

title: puff balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry for several minutes.
Drain and roll in powdered or regular sugar.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes.
Mix the eggs, oil, milk, cake mix and pudding mix thoroughly.
Add grated German chocolate and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased Bundt or tube pan.
When done, let stand 2 hours before removing it from the pan.
Do not invert!!
Good to make ahead of time.
It freezes well.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all in a large pot. Add cinnamon sticks and cloves. Let simmer, then later remove cloves and cinnamon sticks.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange cooked sweet potatoes in large skillet.
Mix together all ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Pat into bottom of pan, evenly.
Put soup over this, then place slices of cheese to cover mixture, then add Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are good and brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cool macaroni; mix with other ingredients.
Chill.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat until well mixed.
Pour into glasses over a scoop of ice cream or crushed ice.
Serve while cold.

title: devil on horseback
directions: Stuff almonds in dates.
Divide bacon strips into thirds. Wrap around dates and secure with toothpicks.
Broil until bacon is done.

title: aunt sue's chocolate chip buttermilk cookies(makes enough for several hungry kids.)
directions: Stir together the flour and soda; set aside.
Cream the sugars and shortening
until
light and fluffy, using mixer at medium speed.
Add
eggs,
one
at
a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend
in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk
to
the
creamed mixture, beating well after each addition,
using
mixer
at
low
speed.
Stir
in chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto greased baking
sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until
golden
brown.
Remove
from
baking sheets. Cool on racks. Makes about 9 dozen cookies.

title: corn bread(my grandmother's recipe)
directions: Mix together and pour into a hot, 12-inch iron skillet.
Bake 25 minutes at 475°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Add potato chips and flour. Roll dough into balls and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes, light to golden brown.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add seasonings.
Add soup, string beans and milk.
Simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add egg noodles; simmer for about 10 minutes, until noodles are cooked.

title: rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice in water with butter and salt for 1/2 hour or until stiff.
Add half and half; cover.
Bring to boil.
Boil 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add to rice and bring to boil.
Remove from stove. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Refrigerate.
(Best when done in a double boiler.)

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries gently.
Drop mixture into muffin pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown at 350°.

title: italian chicken bake
directions: In bowl, mix seasonings with mushrooms, tomatoes, Velveeta cheese and onion.
In 13 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish, mix chicken broth, rice and tomato mixture.
Lay the chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen chopped broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Cook rice.
Combine 2 ingredients.
Add can of mushroom soup, jar of Cheez Whiz and water chestnuts.
Put into casserole and heat.
Before serving, add grated cheese on top.
Put back into oven for cheese to melt.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with seasoned flour. Save remaining flour.
Brown meat in hot fat in a 4-quart saucepan. Add water and cover tightly.
Simmer until meat is tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions, potatoes and carrots. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add peas.
Cover and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Blend 1/4 cup water with remaining flour. Add to stew, stirring gently.
Cook until thickened.

title: easy meal
directions: Make ground beef into 4 patties.
Place on large piece of aluminum foil each patty separate.
Slice onions and potatoes, placing in layers (sliced carrots optional).
Season with salt and pepper.
Close the foil and bake at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: fruity iced tea
directions: In a large pot (do not use aluminum, copper or iron); heat water until it just comes to the boil.
Stir in tea, mint and sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Immediately strain tea through a fine sieve.
Stir in juices.
Let cool to room temperature.
Place tea in one large pitcher or divide between 2 pitchers.
Fill pitchers or glasses with ice and serve.
Garnish each glass with a sprig of mint and a slice of orange.
Makes 10 cups.

title: herbed cheese bites
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Spread mixture onto each cracker just before serving. Makes 15 servings.

title: potato candies
directions: While the mashed potato is still warm, add margarine and blend well.
Mix in flavoring and add enough confectioners sugar to make the batter stiff enough to roll into ball.
Divide and color as desired; flatten balls slightly on top and decorate with a nut or chocolate chips.
You also can cover with chocolate.

title: ann's crazy cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients into ungreased loaf pan, 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inches.
Level out dry ingredients and pour the oil, vinegar and vanilla over them.
Pour the cold water over and mix thoroughly with a fork.
Do not beat.
Bake in same pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. After cake is cool, frost with whipping cream.

title: lasagna pie
directions: Pour cottage cheese on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix hamburg with sweet basil and oregano.
Pour over cottage cheese.
Mix milk, eggs and biscuit.
Pour over hamburg.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Preheat oven to
Cook until crust forms.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix in Crisco and milk.
Add eggs and mix well.
Let rise until double its size. Roll out flat and spread on top with melted butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll up as for jelly roll and cut into slices. Place in greased muffin pans and let rise.
Bake in hot oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and peanut butter in large bowl. Form into small balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips over low heat (steam works best).
Dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan, stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and clear. Remove from heat stir in gelatin.
Cool.
Place strawberries in coated pastry shell.
Pour glaze over berries.
Refrigerate before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: quick jubilee sauce
directions: In small bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Chill. Serve over vanilla ice cream or vanilla pudding.
Makes 1 2/3 cup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in small amount of margarine.
Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 20 or 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: chicken biscuit casserole
directions: Take can of chicken and spread in bottom of baking dish. Arrange biscuits on top of chicken.
Mix chicken soup and milk, then spread over top of biscuits.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Wash parsley; drain and shake out excess moisture.
Soak cracked wheat in warm water in large bowl until it appears dry. Set aside.
Remove stems from parsley; chop fine.
Chop onions fine.
Chop 1 celery stick fine.
Dice tomatoes and 1 cucumber. Squeeze out excess water from cracked wheat and place in large bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Pour 3/4 batter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pie filling.
Spoon remaining batter on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Cook noodles al dente.
Put small amount of sauce in casserole.
Layer noodles, Ricotta and Muenster cheese. Top with sauce (generous amount) and grate all the Mozzarella on top. Bake, covered, about 1 hour. Allow to set a few minutes before serving.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt, beat well.
Gradually add sifted flour, mixing well. Shape into 3/4-inch balls; dip in slightly beaten egg whites, then roll in pecans.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet. Press down center with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes. Cool slightly; remove from pan and cool on rack.
Fill with icing or preserves.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and oil.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to zucchini mixture, blending well.
Stir in nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients together and chill 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Beat in cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip, then stir in bananas.
Layer vanilla wafers and pudding mixture.
Chill in refrigerator and serve.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix frozen lemonade and milk until thick.
Stir in Cool Whip, pour into pie crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: ginger marinade for boneless chicken
directions: Mix together and then marinate boneless chicken in plastic bag for 2 or more hours.
Then broil or grill.
Delicious!

title: mushroom shrimp mold
directions: Melt soup and cream cheese together in double boiler.
Add gelatin to 3 tablespoons water.
Add gelatin to hot mixture.
When hot mixture is blended, add mayonnaise, chopped celery, onion and shrimp.
Put in mold and cool overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: bacon tomato cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Coarsely chop bacon, tomato and onion.
Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Set aside.
Separate each biscuit into three biscuits.
Lay each piece into a mini-muffin pan and press into cup.
Fill each cup with bacon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes about 30.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place in casserole dish in following order; layer of broken chips, tuna (drained), peas (drained) and soup.
Poke a few holes in top and pour in milk.
Place in oven at 350° for 20 minutes, remove.
Place more chips on top and keep in oven until brown, about 5 more minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, but do not brown. Add milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Pour over broccoli, potatoes or other vegetables.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top and heat until melted.
Add a little garlic powder and serve over noodles.

title: elk, venison, or beef meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except 3 tablespoons catsup.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Pur mixture into pan and top with 3 tablespoons catsup.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, rice, egg, salt and pepper.
Form into balls.
Put in pan.
Peel and quarter 4 medium potatoes and place on top of meatballs.
Mix soups and tomato sauce together and pour over potatoes and meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Blend soup with water.
Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture; combine with ground beef, dry bread crumbs, onion, parsley, egg and salt.
Shape into meatballs, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.

title: what's this
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces and put into 9 x 9-inch glass dish.
Make vanilla pudding according to directions. Pour over cake while still hot.
Make jello according to package directions, then pour jello over hot pudding.
Cover with defrosted fruit and place in refrigerator until set.
Serve with whipped cream topping.
(Use frozen strawberries with strawberry jello and frozen raspberries with raspberry jello.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pistachio mix and pineapple juice, plus fold in the whipped topping.
Mix in marshmallows and nuts.
Spoon into pretty bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato bread
directions: Stir yeast into potato water until dissolved.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add potatoes and yeast mixture.
Add salt and milk and mix well. Add flour, 1 cup at a time, until you have a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic. Put dough in an oiled bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan, knocking out excess flour.
Spread evenly the brown sugar and walnuts.
Cream together sugar, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Dissolve and mix cocoa and warm water and add to mixture.
Then add flour, salt, soda and stir well.
Pour over nuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool for a few minutes and then turn onto a rack with topping up.
Serve warm.

title: melon-blueberry salad
directions: Combine watermelon, honeydew and blueberries in deep bowl. Combine honey and lime juice and pour over fruit.
Cover and marinate 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator, stirring several times to distribute marinade evenly.
Drain fruits, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine sour cream and 2 tablespoons liquid, stirring to blend.
Fold into fruit and serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Boil vegetables a few minutes.
Drain and put in casserole. Heat the soups.
Add the Cheez Whiz.
Pour over vegetables and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine butter and sugar in top of double boiler.
Stir in evaporated milk; add chocolate.
Cook over hot water for 30 minutes.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat; beat until creamy. Store in refrigerator and reheat as needed.
Add cream for a thinner sauce.
Yields 1 1/2 pints.

title: cloister creek's spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese wreath
directions: Beat Cheddar cheese and cream cheese with mixer (medium) until well blended.
Add juice, pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Form into wreath.
Garnish with fresh parsley and red bell pepper stars. Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Pour
a little of the scalded milk into egg mixture and stir well.
Return this mixture to scalded milk and mix well.
Add rice, raisins, vanilla and spices. Pour into a buttered 1-quart baking dish; set dish in a shallow pan and pour 1-inch of water into shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Melt in saucepan oleo, Crisco and 1/2 cup water.
Let cool. Dissolve dry yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
In large bowl, beat eggs, 1/2 cup water and sugar.
Add yeast mixture with other ingredients.
Add flour; mix well.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Will rise in 30 minutes.
Place on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Dough will keep for 6 days in refrigerator if well covered.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Remove from skillet.
Place 1 3/4 cups water in skillet on medium heat. Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water in bowl.
Pour in skillet. Bring to a boil.
When thick, add Veg-All and other vegetables and hamburger meat.
Season to taste.
Heat just until vegetables are warm.
Place in long, rectangle glass baking dish.
Line top with potatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip with preserves
directions: Mix all of ingredients together and place preserves of choice or pepper jelly in center.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: jack's grilled barbecue hamburgers
directions: Mix desired amount of ground chuck with enough barbecue sauce for a meat loaf consistency.
Shape into hamburgers.
Place on foil lined barbecue grill that has randomly cut holes in foil.
Add sliced raw onions over the hamburgers.
Cook, turning hamburgers and onions together while cooking until done as desired.
You can add additional barbecue sauce to hamburgers while cooking.
Hot dogs are good cooked this way, too.

title: creole pecan pralines
directions: Cook sugar and evaporated milk together slowly in heavy saucepan until a little of the mixture dropped from spoon into a cup of cold water will form soft ball (240° on candy thermometer). Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.
Add butter and vanilla and beat for a few minutes, then add pecans.
Before candy hardens, drop by spoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper.

title: mother's banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, and shortening. Add mashed banana and buttermilk; blend well. Sift together baking powder, salt, soda, and flour. Add flour mixture to dough 1 cup at a time; mixing well after each addition. Add nuts and flavoring/extract, stir in. Bake at 325 degrees in pan sprayed with Pam.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple, cherry pie filling, pecans and coconut and pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and butter or margarine with pastry blender and sprinkle on top.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Layer ice cream sandwiches in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Top with Cool Whip. Dribble with caramel and chocolate syrup. Top with walnuts (and/or pecans). Freeze.

title: seafood curry with beer
directions: Combine beef, 2 tablespoons tomato sauce, egg, bread crumbs and salt.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
In skillet, lightly brown meatballs and drain fat.
Stir in remaining tomato sauce, mixed vegetables, thyme and pepper; simmer 5 minutes.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat thoroughly.

title: baked rigatoni
directions: Cook rigatoni according to directions.
Layer noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Repeat layers and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let yeast stand for 5 minutes; mix in dry ingredients (except flour).
Add water, oil, yeast and then add flour and mix well.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down and let rise another 30 minutes; make into rolls.
Bake at 500°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add in other ingredients and stir.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: graduation punch(for purdue or norwell with their gold and black colors.)
directions: Mix above ingredients in a punch bowl and add chilled ginger ale to taste.
One can make ice rings ahead from apricot nectar and freeze them in Ziploc bags for use in the bowls of punch. Punch is not too sweet.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rich butter wafers
directions: Beat butter and sugar together. Beat in egg and vanilla. Gradually stir flour into butter mixture.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Place them on a greased baking sheet.
Decorate each cookie with a nut meat.
Bake them in a moderate oven at 375° until edges are light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in stuffing.
Boil chicken breasts and cut into pieces, save broth.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons butter.
Chill for easy handling.
Shape in 2-inch balls with a marshmallow inside each.
Use 1/4 cup of potatoes to cover.
Heat honey and 1 tablespoon butter in a small skillet over high heat. When syrup is hot, add potato balls 1 at a time.
Roll in glaze, coating completely.
Roll in nuts.
Space balls, so they do not touch, in a greased shallow baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: microwave cheesy chicken
directions: Place 1 T butter in an 11 X 7 X 2 inch microwave safe dish; set aside.
Combine cracker crumbs and pepper.
Dip chicken in remaining butter then spread with sour cream.
Roll chicken in the crumb mixture.
Place in prepared dish.
Cover loosely and microwave on high for 6-7 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.
Let stand for 5-10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: pecans
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: candy shop pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice cookie dough and spread out dough into a 12 to 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake 20 to 24 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheese tater pie
directions: Mix meat and bread crumbs with milk, egg, salt, dry mustard and onion.
When mixed, press the mixture in an 8-inch pie tin. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Place 3 slices of cheese on meat.
Prepare mashed potatoes and swirl on top of cheese.
Break the fourth slice of cheese on top of potatoes. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: shrimp soup
directions: ("Chupe de Camarones," a Peruvian recipe given to me by my mother-in-law.)
Delicious with or without the pepper.

title: bunue los(sweet treats)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large plastic bag, mixing well and set aside.
Cut flour tortillas into 3 (12-inch) strips; fry a few at a time in hot oil until crisp and golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
While they are still hot place a few at a time in the bag that has the sugar mixture and shake gently to coat them.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: buttermilk fruit salad
directions: Mix milk, pudding mix, and cool whip together first. Add remaining ingredients.

title: shrimp dip
directions: *Can substitute 12 ounces frozen cocktail shrimp.

title: french coffee cake
directions: Cream together sugar, salt, shortening and vanilla.
Add gradually in small amounts a portion of the liquid alternately with the flour.
Add eggs and mix until smooth.
The sides of the bowl should be scraped down occasionally to insure a uniform batter. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend together cornstarch and sugar.
Combine with water in saucepan.
Cool until thick (3 to 5 minutes).
Add jello to mixture and stir until dissolved.
Allow to cool but not completely cold. Clean strawberries and spread evenly in baked pie shell.
Pour cooled, cooked mixture over all.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
If desired, serve with whipped topping.
Can also be used with peaches (apricot jello).

title: potato salad
directions: Put potatoes in pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.
Drain and cool, then peel.
Stir together mayonnaise, mustard, eggs, celery, onion and relish.
Add potatoes and toss.
Season with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour to 24 hours before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: potatoes anna
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, chop onion.
Peel and slice white and sweet potatoes, keeping in separate piles.

In a nonstick 10-inch skillet with ovensafe handle (or wrap with double thickness of heavy duty foil) in hot salad oil, cook onion until tender. With a slotted spoon, remove onion to bowl and set aside.
In remaining oil in skillet, arrange white potatoes in layer, overlapping slices.
Sprinkle sauteed onions over potatoes.
Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine or butter and sprinkle with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Arrange sweet potato slices over white potato layer.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper, and add onion as with white potatoes.
Continue layers until potatoes run out.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine eggs, milk, oil and lemon flavoring.
Add dry jello and add cake mix and mix well; pour into tube pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let cool before turning onto plate.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients and let stand 15 minutes.
Chop cranberries in half.
Mix well.
Spoon batter into 24 muffin cups with liners, filling to top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and butter.
Sift cocoa and confectioners sugar and add to mixture; mix well.
Add pecans and mix.
Butter 2 (9 x 12) Pyrex dishes and press candy into dishes.
Let stand overnight and cut into squares.

title: snack
directions: Boil together Karo syrup, sugar and oleo for one minute and then add soda.
Blend well and pour over crackers and peanuts. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir a few times while baking.

title: banana creme pie
directions: Slice bananas into small circular pieces, then dip the slices into the lemon juice to help prevent the bananas from turning black.
Layer the bottom and sides of the pie crust with the banana slices.
Cook Eagle Brand milk, cornstarch, eggs and water in a medium saucepan.
When mixture starts to bubble, add butter and vanilla flavoring.
Stir quickly; cook until almost thick. Let cool, then add to pie crust.
When entire pie is cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: pepper relish
directions: Mix peppers and onions together.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 10 minutes; drain.
Cover again with boiling water and bring all ingredients back to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with pepper/onion mixture and cook over medium heat about 15 minutes. Ladle into pint jars and seal while hot.
Makes 6 pints.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Stir in egg, onion and cayenne pepper.
Add your buttermilk; beat well.
Heat oil in heavy cast-iron frypan.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of batter into hot oil.
Fry until brown. Drain on paper towel (to remove any excess oil).

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: g'mom weaver's (cora minibel) filled jumbo drops - 1925(great-grandmother to our kids)
directions: Drop by teaspoon; flatten with fingers.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon filling on cookie and top with 1/2 teaspoon dough.

title: hawaiian surprise
directions: Spread	pineapple
in
bottom
of
an
8 x 13-inch pan. Spread cherry pie filling on top.	Spread cake mix (dry) next. Cut
up the butter; place on top, then walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Layer noodles, onion, corned beef (flaked) and cheese.
Spread soup over top.
Crush a few crackers or chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in remaining ingredients in order listed.
Fill pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise.
Melt half the butter in a heavy saucepan on medium heat.
Coat each piece of potato with melted butter.
Turn each piece several times, cooking slowly on top of stove.
When potato begins to tender, add brown sugar and molasses, mixing thoroughly with potato slices.
Add water, salt and nutmeg.
Cook about 5 more minutes.
Transfer potatoes to a casserole dish, putting orange slices between the two layers of potatoes.
Cover with syrup; dot with rest of butter.
Place in oven at 350° and bake 20 minutes and cover.

title: jerry's sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake to mix.
Good on pork, chicken and baked potatoes.

title: blueberry crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients; cut in butter.
Add egg and mix to make crumbs. Place half the crumb mixture in pan.
Pour over it, distributing evenly, the blueberry filling. Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious served warm with ice cream.

title: cabbage cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, brown together ground beef and onion. Drain.
Using a large oven dish, place ground beef on bottom. Spread cabbage wedges over the meat.
Mix together the tomato sauce and garlic salt.
Pour over the cabbage.
Cover tightly and cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Place grated cheese on top.
Return to oven and melt cheese.
Bake to lightly brown.
Serve over bed of cooked rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion; drain well.
Add the remaining ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: perfect meat loaf
directions: Mix everything but 8 ounces of tomato sauce.
Shape into loaf. Place in shallow pan.
Chill for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over loaf and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: irish caraway raisin bread
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add butter and crumble with fingertips or blender.
Beat egg; add sour cream, milk (room temperature) together.
Fold into 1st mixture.
Add floured raisins and caraway seeds.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in heavy pan; add milk and stir. Cook over low heat.
Stir egg yolks together and add a little of the hot pudding to them.
Mix and return it to the hot pudding. Bring mixture to a slow boil and cook 2 minutes.
If it gets lumpy beat with mixer.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and butter. Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: special turkey dressing
directions: Mix well.
Stuff the turkey.
Bake at 350° until the popcorn blows the a-- off the turkey.

title: aunt mamie's salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool, then add rest of ingredients except Cool Whip.
When partially set, fold in Cool Whip.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat again.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add pecans and coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 3 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix dressing mix with mayonnaise.
Add to cottage cheese. Chill at least 1 hour.
May be garnished with dill weed.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with garlic, oregano and basil on both sides; rub it in.
Dip chicken breasts into egg and then into bread crumbs.
Fry until cooked.
In baking dish, place chicken across the bottom; spoon spaghetti sauce onto each piece and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese across the top and broil until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Drain okra and lima beans. Add to all other ingredients in large pot. Heat on medium until hot.

title: cranberry citrus punch
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Garnish with lemon or orange slices.
Yields 25 servings. Preparation time is 15 minutes.

title: variable stack cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour four (9-inch) round cake pans.
(Tip:
Use cocoa instead of flour to eliminate white spots on bottom and sides.)
Divide batter evenly among pans and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together, add eggs and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients, then cereals, coconut and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet, and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients to beef mixture.
Simmer in large boiler for about 1 hour.
Serve topped with sour cream or grated cheese.
Freezes well for meals when we need a break from the kitchen.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Fry onion; mix with cheese, meat and egg. Roll out dough and fill with mixture.
Roll and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Slice and serve.

title: easy oven baked potatoes
directions: Mix all together, put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine butter, Corn Chex crumbs and cheese; set aside. Combine soup, onions, parsley and seasoning.
Stir in zucchini and 2/3 cups Chex mix.
Mix well; turn into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until zucchini is tender and Chex are golden brown.

title: cranberry pork roast
directions: Mix all ingredients except pork in a 3-quart or larger slow cooker. Add pork; spoon some of the cranberry mixture over top. Cook and cover on low for 6 to 8 hours or until pork is tender. Remove pork to a cutting board and slice. Serve sauce with pork.

title: hard christmas candy
directions: Stir the sugar, syrup and water until dissolved.
Boil to 295° on candy thermometer; remove from heat.
Add the oil and desired food coloring.
Pour onto cookie sheet covered with 4x sugar. Break into pieces.

title: italian eggplant(diabetic)
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick spray. Remove peel of eggplant and slice into circles. Dip circle in egg beater then into breadcrumbs. Place each round in skillet and brown on both sides. Place in ovenproof casserole, putting a generous tablespoon of spaghetti sauce on each eggplant round. Stack if necessary. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and brown. Remove from drippings. Blend sugar, flour, salt and pepper together.
Add to drippings. Stir to make a smooth paste. Add vinegar and water.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine sauce, sliced potatoes and onions.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 to 4 hours.
Sprinkle with bacon bits just before serving.

title: ham and pickle roll-ups
directions: Let pickles drain and then dry them off with paper towel. Wipe ham to remove water from each slice.
Soften cream cheese so you can spread.
Lay ham out and spread cream cheese over one side, then place pickle on one end and roll up.
Place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours and then slice.

title: meal-in-a-bowl chicken soup
directions: Bring broth to boil over high heat; add carrots and celery. Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Add peas, corn, chicken and potatoes. Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir in macaroni, pepper and parsley. Heat through.
Makes 2 quarts.
Serves 4.

title: lemon barbecued meat loaves
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine the ground chuck, bread cubes, lemon juice, onion, egg and salt.
Mix well and shape into 6 individual loaves.
Arrange on a greased 9 X 13 inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: sinful cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
When cake comes out of oven, use meat fork or wooden spoon to poke holes in the cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the cake, then pour caramel topping over the cake while hot.
Let cool for 1 or 2 hours, then top with Cool Whip.
Crunch up three Heath candy bars; sprinkle over the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and spread on the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Then spread pepperoni, onion and cheese on top. Melt in the microwave or oven until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with Triscuits, pita chips or other chips or crackers.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine boiling water and oatmeal and cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine all together.
Let rise twice in bowl and once in pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add grated garlic and onion.
Add Worcestershire sauce and crab meat.
Chill a few hours before serving with Wheat Thins or other crackers.

title: easy jambalaya
directions: Heat oil over medium heat; cook sausage until brown.
Add chicken, onion, pepper, celery and garlic.
Saute until chicken is done.
Add tomatoes, okra and sauce and seasoning.
Boil and stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir and serve.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Drain smallest size green olives.
Push thumb in biscuit. Flour hands; roll closed around olive.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: mint frosting
directions: Blend peppermint extract and green food coloring into the Cool Whip.
Frost tops of 2 (8-inch) layers or tops and sides of an 8-inch square cake.
Garnish with mint leaves and chocolate curls, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 1/4 cup butter.
Add cheese and melt.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Mix in the potatoes.
Do not beat.
Top with the corn flake crumbs, mixed with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt; drain well.
Combine spinach, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over spinach mixture.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove casserole from refrigerator for 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, eggs and flavorings.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with Pam or floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While hot, glaze with:

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello with the boiling water.
Add other ingredients. (May need to add small amount of jello to make it firmer.)
Place in molds and refrigerate.

title: barbecued london broil
directions: Combine marinade ingredients; pour over meat in large plastic container or plastic marinating bag.
Refrigerate, turning occasionally, at least 8 hours or overnight.
When grill is ready, remove meat and pat dry, reserving marinade.
Grill according to desired doneness, about 25 minutes for rare.
Place reserved marinade in small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Skim any oil from the top and serve with the meat that has been sliced thin diagonally across the grain.

title: zucchini squash italian casserole
directions: Add salt and pepper to taste to squash.
Saute onion and green peppers in butter.
Combine onion and green peppers with all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into Pam-sprayed casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Tasty when served over rice.

title: herbed chicken and broccoli(servings:  4)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with Italian seasoning.
Pound between sheets of wax paper.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Spray nonstick skillet. Cook and stir chicken strips just until no longer pink.
Set aside.
In small saucepan, whisk small amount of milk into flour. Stir remaining milk with garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add cheese; stir.
Spray 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread about 1/4 cup sauce in bottom of dish.
Arrange broccoli over sauce, then chicken pieces.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Calories:
Fat:
3 grams.

title: florentine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup of boiling water.
Stir in vinegar, mayonnaise and salt.
Cool until almost firm.
Beat, then add spinach, onion, celery and cottage cheese.
Chill until firm. Red wine vinegar and Marzetti slaw dressing can be used instead of mayonnaise and regular vinegar.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add coffee; boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into 1/2-gallon container.
Add vodka and vanilla.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Whip in mixer.
Pour into oblong Pyrex and refrigerate.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Simmer onions in hamburger.
Add chili powder, paprika and tomato juice.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: prairie raisin cake
directions: Boil together
for 10 minutes the raisins, water, sugar and shortening;
allow	to cool.
Add flour and other ingredients, except
nuts.
Add	2
eggs, if needed.
Add nuts.	Turn into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice and chops
directions: Brown pork chops and bell pepper in skillet.
Add rice, salt and tomato sauce.
Stir in water.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes until meat is done.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: In bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons oleo until smooth.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken and twist slightly to seal edges.
Brush with 1 tablespoon oleo and dip in crouton crumbs. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: barbecue shrimp and bacon
directions: In a bowl, add 1/2 jar of barbecue sauce to 1 pound of shrimp. Fry bacon.
Set aside.
Drain grease from pan.
Place shrimp and remaining sauce in hot frying pan.
Cover and cook for 6 minutes. Remove lid.
Add bacon and cheese.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 minutes. Serve hot.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Combine rice and corn; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Add ground beef and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can of water.
Cover with bacon.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake for 15 to 30 minutes, until bacon is crisp.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix chocolate syrup, flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in a jelly roll pan.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Alternately add flour and milk to sugar mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.

title: beer bread
directions: Beat well.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine.
Let boil for 15 minutes or until it forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Beat until creamy. Pour in buttered pan (13 x 9-inch).
Let cool and cut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into ball and roll in crushed nuts, if desired.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
Combine the flour, salt and pepper. Coat meat in flour mixture.
In large skillet, cook meat in hot oil until browned on all sides.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid. Add tomato juice, water, onion and garlic to meat in skillet. Cover and simmer for 1 1/4 hours until the meat is tender. Uncover and stir in Worcestershire sauce.
Add pepper strips. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
If necessary, thick gravy with flour and cold water.
Add drained tomatoes and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in double boiler, then cool.
Beat eggs and sugar until lemon colored; add the flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion; pour off fat. Blend in pizza sauce and garlic salt.
Put mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
In a small bowl mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour.
Pour over meat mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; stir together soup and cheese. Gradually add milk, egg and mayonnaise.
Add mixture to drained broccoli; mix lightly and pour into buttered casserole pan (8 x 8-inches or 10 x 10-inches).
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° approximately.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Crumble beef into heated skillet and cook over medium heat until meat loses red color.
Add onion, celery and garlic during last 5 minutes cooking time.
Drain grease.
Drain tomatoes, reserving 3/4 cup juice and mix juice with cornmeal.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces, add cornmeal mixture and cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add corn with its liquid, olives with liquid, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and meat mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole, sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sand bucket cake
directions: Crush cookies well, to resemble sand.
You can put in a blender.
Set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip. Combine cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture.
Mix well.
Use a child's sand bucket to serve in.
Now layer in bucket: cookies, mixture, cookies, mixture and end with cookies so it looks like a bucket of sand.
Serve with a sand shovel. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs, flour, baking soda and extract well.
Chill.
Roll into balls on lightly floured waxed paper to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into favorite shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. In small baking dish, pour in beef and cover with pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs together, then pour over meat mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs.
Add oil and pumpkin; beat until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients; gradually beat into pumpkin mixture.
Pour batter into five 5 x 2 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire racks to cool completely.	Yields 5 miniature loaves.

title: creamy spinach and carrot soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add onions.

Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender (5 to 6 minutes). Stir in flour until smooth and bubbly (1 minute). Stir in half and half and chicken broth. Add remaining ingredients except orange peel. Continue cooking over low heat, stirring occasionally, until soup is heated through (12 to 15 minutes). Garnish with zest or strip of orange peel.
Serves 4.

title: apple and pecan filled acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half crosswise and remove seeds.
Cut bottom of each squash half to sit flat, if necessary.
Place squash halves, cut side up in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add hot water to dish of 1-inch deep.
Combine apples and next 3 ingredients; spoon evenly into squash halves.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until squash is tender.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: tommy's favorite baked chicken
directions: Mix together oatmeal, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Place this mixture in a shallow dish.
In a separate, shallow dish, place milk.
Place chicken, one piece at a time, in oatmeal mixture, then dip in milk and again in the oatmeal mixture.
Place chicken in large baking dish, lightly greased (I use Pam spray).
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: my mother's stuffed eggplant
directions: Hollow eggplant by cutting in half and carefully scooping out of shell.
Reserve shell by placing both halves in aluminum foil-lined baking dish.
Dice eggplant, bacon, tomato, garlic and onion.
Saute bacon and onion in frypan and add eggplant and tomato.
Beat egg in large bowl.
Add eggplant mixture, half crumbs and half cheese.
Place in shell halves.
Top with remaining crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add shortening and milk.
Blend for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Add flour (6 cups).
Knead, cover with waxed paper and wet towel.
Let rise 3 hoursor overnight in the refrigerator.
Punch down, make into rolls, and let rise.
Bake at 300 degrees for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook rice.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger.
Add chili powder, onion, green pepper and 1 can tomato sauce.
Mix rice and hamburger together.
Sprinkle on cheese and 1 can of tomato sauce on top.
Warm in oven until cheese is melted.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches; reserve syrup.
Combine syrup, vinegar, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then lower temperature.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over peach halves and let cool.
Chill before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter and pour over muffin mix; add cream-style corn, 4 eggs and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix the ingredients well.
In a 2-quart casserole, cover bottom with one layer of onion sliced thin; pour 1/2 of the mixture over onions and put another layer of onions, then pour remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
When top is light brown, pudding is done. Remove from oven and serve warm.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Make the night before to allow flavors to penetrate layers. Refrigerate, covered.

title: fruit cake
directions: Beat
butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg yolks. Mix mace
with flour and add flour, whiskey, alternately.
Mix nuts and
fruit
in
1/3 cup flour then add to other mix.
Beat egg whites stiff;
add
cup sugar.
Fold into cake batter. Bake in tube
pan
at
for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 tube cakes.

title: hockey dance dip
directions: Hollow out loaf of bread.
Save chunks for dipping.
Mix all ingredients and put in bread hollow.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and milk together.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch chips and stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut into small squares.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cut toast into diagonal pieces and dip into the dip mixture.
Taste like bacon, lettuce and tomato sandwich.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg and beat well.
Dissolve baking soda in can of tomato soup.
Add alternately with flour, raisins, nuts, cinnamon and cloves.
Bake 3/4 of an hour at 350°.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger; saute bacon, but not too crisp.
Fry onion slightly in bacon fat.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a covered baking dish 35 minutes at 350°.
Stir beans, twice during baking.
Hamburger may be omitted and 1 pound hot dogs may be added instead.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Break califlower into small pieces.
Cook until just tender, drain an place in a 2 Qt. casserole dish.
3 Tbsp.
butter in pan and stir in flour to make a paste.
Blend in milk and slowly bring to a boil and simmer until thickened.
Add salt and pepper and pour over cauliflower.
Mix together stuffing, water and melted butter and spoon over top of casserole.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peas oriental
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Precook peas briefly; drain.
Mix all ingredients (except onion rings) in covered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Crumble onion rings over top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 10 more minutes.

title: pineapple cheddar salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sugar and pineapple; cool.
While cooling, whip cream and grate the cheese. Fold into gelatin mixture.
Add pecans.
Spoon into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except apples.
Fold in chopped apples. Place in a well-greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 35 minutes at 250°.
Cool and pour on sauce.

title: 14 day icicle pickles
directions: Let pickles stand in 1 quart boiling water with salt 1 week. Drain and cover with boiling water for 24 hours, then drain again and cover with boiling water and alum.
Let stand another 24 hours, then drain.
Take sugar, vinegar and spices.
Turn over the pickles boiling hot and let stand 24 hours.
Repeat 4 days. Doesn't have to seal.

title: unbaked pineapple cheesecake
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar well.
Drain pineapple well, heat juice and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Chill the Jell-O mixture until the consistency of egg whites.
Put with the cheese mixture.
Add lemon juice.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Save 1/2 cup crumbs.
Press the rest in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour in mixture and top with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Chill well.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
In pan, mix 1/2 cup pineapple juice with eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Stir in lemon juice. Refrigerate until cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Lightly mix in pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and grapes.
Cover.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Put can of cherries in pan, then can of pineapple.
Put cake mix on top (powder form).
Melt butter and pour on top of cake mix.
On top of that, put coconut and nuts.

title: dad's steak and gravy
directions: Roll steak in flour and salt and pepper.
Brown in Crisco oil. Remove from pan and place in Dutch oven.
Add a little more flour to grease in frying pan like you are going to make gravy.
Add water and Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour over steak and bake 3 hours at 350°, covered.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; put in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Season beef with salt and pepper.
Mix with onion.
Cook in margarine or oil until meat is browned.
Put vegetable chicken soup in baking dish.
Spread ground beef mixture in a layer over soup.
Put layer of mashed potatoes over meat.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook chicken; dice and set aside.
Cook celery, onion and mushrooms in oil until crisp and tender.
Blend cornstarch, water, consomme and soy sauce with wire whisk.
Stir into the chopped vegetables.
Add meat.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion; drain off all fat. Cut peppers in halves and remove seeds.
Cook in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain peppers.
Add cracker crumbs, egg, catsup, salt and pepper to ground beef.
Fill peppers with ground beef mixture, put in baking dish and add small amount of water. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: whiskey cookies
directions: Make small crescents.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Great Christmas cookie.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar, then fold in Cool Whip. spread on the cooked base.
Mix together strawberry jello and boiling water and add strawberries.
Let jello stand for 10 minutes or until jelled a bit and spread on top.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: red velvet punch
directions: Place tea bags in a large container.
Cover, let stand overnight, then remove tea bags gently.
Combine tea with cranberry apple drink, pina colada mix, lemon or lime juice and sugar.
Keep chilled.
When ready to serve, pour over ice in punch bowl; add soda and garnish with fruit.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Pour into empty foil roll tray.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomato paste, water and spices to taste.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on bun.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crust:
Cut oleo into flour until well blended.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: world's best cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand for 5 minutes. Dissolve sugar and butter in warm milk.
Add eggs, 2 cups of flour and yeast mixture and beat until smooth.
Continue adding flour gradually, working dough until all flour is moistened.
Dough should be dry and not too moist.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Place dough in lightly greased bowl, turning to coat.
Cover, and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Turn dough out on lightly floured surface, knead until smooth, and let rise again until double in size (about 1 hour).

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain and pour boiling water over again.
Drain at once.
Cook with vinegar, sugar and salt thoroughly for 20 minutes.
Jar and seal while hot.

title: grandma kay's cran-raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Use any type of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch or even 10 x 8-inch pan or dish.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serve with Mushroom Sauce (following). Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy maple candy
directions: Set the margarine out of the refrigerator to soften.
Mix softened margarine in a bowl with the frosting mix and maple flavoring.
Knead the mixture with hands or mixer until it is well mixed.
Pinch off mixture, roll it into a small ball and roll ball in chopped nuts.

title: coquilles st. jacques
directions: Toss bread crumbs with 1 tablespoon melted margarine; set aside.
Stir together next 4 ingredients; set aside.
In medium skillet, over medium-high heat, cook scallops in 2 tablespoons margarine until opaque.
Remove.
Drain well.
Cook mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine for 3 minutes.
Add to cheese mixture with scallops.
Spoon into 6 individual baking dishes or shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Broil 6 inches from source of heat for 2 to 4 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange supreme salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water;
cool.
Add 1/2 cup juice from fruit and orange
juice.
Chill slightly.
Fold in fruit. Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare pie filling as directed.
Cool. Whip cream and fold into pie filling.
Spread over Jell-O salad. Top with grated cheese.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in strips 1/2-inch wide.
Brown lightly in hot butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add whole can of mushrooms and juice, bouillon cube, 1 cup water and salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
(Cook noodles separately.) Blend sour cream and flour and stir into meat mixture.
Cook just until thickened.
May need to add a little water.
Serve over noodles.

title: pancakes deluxe
directions: Scald milk; add butter and crumbs; let stand until crumbs are soft.
Combine all the other ingredients into this mixture.
Bake on lightly greased griddle.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: grandma's german coffee cake
directions: Blend ingredients - reserve 1 cup of mixture for topping.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper until well done.
Cook pasta and drain.
Drain ground beef if needed.
Combine meat, sauce and pasta with 1 cup of cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, onion, sugar and dill in a mixing bowl. Beat egg with milk.
Add to dry ingredients along with the wine and oleo.
Beat dough until well blended.

title: real hot cocoa
directions: In saucepan, mix cocoa, sugar, salt and water.
Bring to a boil, over low heat.
Boil gently 2 minutes, stirring.
Add milk; heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Just before serving, beat with a hand beater until smooth and foamy.
Add vanilla.
Makes 9 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl in sequence listed and mix well.
Put the mixture in baking pans and heat.
Cook at 375° until it's golden brown and no mixture comes out on a toothpick.
Cool and frost, if desired.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat 2 cups pear juice (add water to make 2 cups).
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool until almost set.
Put jello, pears and cheese in blender.
Pour into bowl and fold in whipped cream and chill.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool, peel and cube.
Layer potatoes, onion, sliced cheese and croutons in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour milk and melted margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and parsley flakes over top.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble into pie crust. Arrange Swiss cheese over bacon.
Beat eggs in bowl slightly with rotary beater; add half and half, salt and pepper.
Blend together.
Pour ingredients over bacon and cheese in pie crust. Bake in moderately hot 400° oven for approximately 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove while center still appears soft and allow to cool slightly before cutting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all ingredients except can of soup.
Put into a casserole dish and pour can of soup over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together margarine and flour for pastry and press into 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix together cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Spread on warm crust.
Mix together pudding and milk and spread over second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash, onions and pepper in thin slices. Cover with salt water and soak for 15 minutes.
Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to a rolling boil. Drain vegetables.
After soaking, add to boiling water for 10 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar, peanut butter, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoon about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: southern fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together and coat fruit and nuts in flour.
Mix sugar and butter and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well each time.
Add rum flavoring.
Pour this over fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Put in 10-inch pan and bake 2 3/4 to 3 hours at 275°.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and apples.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add nuts.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Make corn bread per package directions.
Cool and crumble. Set aside.
Combine tomatoes, green pepper, onion, pickles and bacon.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Stir well and set aside.

title: spinach dip(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir to mix well.
Cover; chill. Makes 3 cups.
To make Swiss Spinach Dip, add 1 1/2 cups shredded Swiss cheese.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Warm spaghetti sauce.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place cooked macaroni; sprinkle hamburger over macaroni.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over hamburger, then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over the top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: low-calorie soup(low fat)
directions: Cut up all the vegetables in chunk size pieces.
Place in a large pot with enough water to cover; boil 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and let simmer until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper and hot sauce as desired.
Tasty and filling, but very low in calories!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place half of the package of Doritos in a baking dish.
Brown ground beef with chili powder and garlic salt.
Place ground beef mixture over chips and add chopped onion, beans and half of the Cheddar cheese.
Place remaining chips over other ingredients. Layer next with Ro-Tel, cream of chicken soup mixture and the rest of the Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dwayne's chili
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and pepper to taste, possibly a little garlic powder, too.
Add other spices and cook for 30 minutes or until all flavors have blended.

title: confetti chicken casserole
directions: Heat soups, milk, onion, pimento and green pepper in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add chicken, macaroni and margarine; mix well.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: rick's taco salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, kidney beans, tomatoes, Tostados, green onion, Catalina dressing and black olives.
Serve with burger (taco seasoning) and sour cream.
Makes 3 to 4 servings, or double ingredients for a larger crowd.
Enjoy!!

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix altogether except cheese.
Put in buttered casserole. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes until hot and cheese is lightly browned.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat 2 eggs; add 2 cups buttermilk, teaspoon soda, 2 cups corn meal and teaspoon salt.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan in 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour. Fold in flour as needed to form a slightly firm batter. Fry on hot griddle.

title: layered dinner
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with potatoes on bottom, then celery, onion, pepper and beef (seasoned).
Top with tomatoes, chopped with juice.
Bake in a large covered dish for 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: stir-fried chicken bowl
directions: Heat oil and saute chicken, garlic and green onions for two minutes over medium heat in a large nonstick skillet or wok.
Add water chestnuts and broccoli; stir-fry 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: spicy salami
directions: Dust
salami
with
flour.
Mix rest of ingredients and saute over low heat until all mixed.
Add salami.
Can be done in crock-pot and served this way.

title: spicy fried chicken
directions: Combine water and hot sauce. Pour over chicken breasts; marinate 1 hour in refrigerator, turning once. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients. Remove chicken from marinade; dredge each piece in flour mixture, coating well. Heat 1 inch of oil in a skillet to 350°; add chicken and fry 5 to 6 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts. Shape into balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° about 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: peanut butter chocolate truffles
directions: Prepare pound cake according to mix instructions.
Pour into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Completely cool cake.
In a large bowl, mix melted margarine, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and confectioners sugar until crumbly.
Add milk, a little at a time, until creamy. Spread evenly over cooled pound cake.
Melt chocolate chips; spread evenly over peanut butter mixture.
Let stand at room temperature, until chocolate hardens.
Cut into bars.
Freezes well.

title: daniel boone's favorite smothered chicken
directions: Disjoint chicken as for
frying.
Season
with salt and pepper and a dash of paprika.
Roll in flour and brown quickly in fat. Then place	in
baking
dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover the dish tightly and bake in a hot oven for about 2 hours or until chicken is	tender.
When it is done, uncover and brown top.
Add more
milk	while
cooking	if necessary. Serve from the baking dish.
Chicken
may
be
cooked
in
the morning for one hour and an	hour
before
dinner returned to oven to finish cooking.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Brown meat in pan.
Cut up all vegetables.
Put all ingredients in a large crock-pot and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 4 1/2 to 6 hours.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Add the beets and cook again real good, then seal.
Add salt if needed.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in lard until crumbly.
Gradually add water and toss together until dough can be gathered into a ball.
If necessary, add more water (1 tablespoon at a time).
Knead dough 15 to 20 times.
Let rest 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients with squash, then add to egg mixture.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick fix
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and then drain.
Put back in skillet and add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then turn down on medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Cook until water is gone and noodles are done.
Serve topped with shredded cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir occasionally while setting so it mixes well.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Make crust of butter, flour and pecans. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: graham and peanut butter bon-bons
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almond bark, in a mixing bowl. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt almond bark.
Form peanut butter mixture into balls and dip in almond bark.
Place on waxed paper. Allow almond bark to cool and firm.

title: chili-stuffed peppers(low-fat, low calorie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut peppers lengthwise in half.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Place peppers, cut side up, in rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cook ground beef and onion in a 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Divide beef mixture evenly among peppers.
Cover and bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until peppers are tender.
Yields 4 servings (2 pepper halves each).

title: baked ham sauce
directions: Mix and serve on baked ham.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 c. evaporated milk, and the pecans, stirring with a spoon until a dough forms. Press half the dough into the baking dish and bake for 6 minutes, reserving the remaining dough.

Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, melt the caramels with the remaining 1/3 c. evaporated milk over medium heat, stirring frequently. Remove the baking dish from the oven and sprinkle the chocolate chips over the warm dough. Spread the melted caramel mixture over the chips, then crumble the remaining dough over the top.
Bake for 20 minutes. Let cool, then refrigerate for at least 1 hour before cutting.

title: quick peanut brittle
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet. Spread peanuts on cookie sheet. In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together remaining ingredients. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring occasionally. Boil gently over medium heat for 14 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over peanuts.
Cool and break into pieces.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Cover biscuits in boiling water and soak until soft.
Add sugar, melted butter, beaten eggs and flavorings.
Mix well.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend powdered sugar with creamed butter; add eggs (one at a time, beating after each).
Mix in flour and vanilla.
Beat well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pan.

title: homemade chili
directions: Mix Old Plantation sausage seasoning in raw meat to taste. Brown meat
in skillet.
Add bell pepper, onions, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic, sweet basil, ground cumin and salt.
Put in crock-pot; cover with water (about 3 cups).
Add flour to thicken and chili powder.
May add chili beans.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Heat chocolate and butter until completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate mix until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 fudgy brownies.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small bite-sized pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given. Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top as you would frosting. Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours. At serving time, garnish with bacon.

title: to clean silver
directions: Line pan completely with aluminum foil.
Put in 3 tablespoons of Spic-N-Span and enough water to cover articles.
Soak for a short while.
Rinse and polish.

title: poke sallet
directions: Cook poke 5 minutes in the 1 cup of water. Drain. Beat the egg.
Dip poke in the egg and roll in the meal. Fry in the bacon grease until brown.

title: lemon 7-up salad
directions: Make jello and place in a 9 x 13 pan.
After jello has set, slice bananas and place on top of jello.
Thicken pineapple juice with a little cornstarch and let cool, then fold into Cool Whip; spread over bananas and jello.
May be garnished with chopped nuts or shredded cheese.

title: jiffy imperial fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir milk into pudding.
Add butter or margarine.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and gradually beat in powdered sugar.
Quickly spread in pan and let set until firm. Refrigeration makes fudge firmer, but is not necessary.
Makes about 24 pieces.

title: broiled crab cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix crab with lemon juice.
Blend mayonnaise with milk and salt; add to crab.
Mix lightly with fork.
Arrange bread or muffin slices on broiler rack.
Brown on one side; turn over. Spread crab mixture on untoasted side.
Add tomato slice and top with cheese; slice.
Broil until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in pecans.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions and drain. Mix with cheese, mayonnaise, celery, and onion.
Put in buttered casserole dish and sprinkle top with crushed crackers.
Pour butter on top and bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: sausage and rice supreme
directions: Fry sausage in skillet; crumble.
Remove sausage from pan; in drippings, saute onion and celery.
Add almonds and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake, covered, in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp, mushroom and artichoke casserole
directions: Melt
2 1/2 tablespoons butter and saute mushrooms; set aside. Boil
and
peel
shrimp.
In
quart casserole, make layer each of artichokes, shrimp and mushrooms.
Make sauce by melting
tablespoons butter, stirring with wire whisk, add flour, then
milk and cream.
Stir until thick; add wine, Worcestershire, salt
and
pepper
to cream sauce.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Sprinkle
top
with grated cheese, then paprika. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice. Better made day before.
Serves 6.
