title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Chill milk until cold, then whip.
Heat juice, gelatin and sugar until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add to whipped milk.
Add strawberries last.
Mix well.
Pour into your prepared crust made from vanilla wafers.
Place in refrigerator until set up.

title: jambo burgers a la tomahawk
directions: Utensils Needed:
Two frying pans, paring knife, spatula, wax paper, 8-quart kettle, can opener, large stirring spoon, measuring spoons and measuring cup.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut core out of cabbage.
Peel off 6 leaves and drop in large kettle of boiling water and cook about 5 minutes.
Lift out and drain on paper towels.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Heat to a boil the butter, cocoa and Coke.
Pour over flour mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter the bottom of a 10-inch glass pie pan.
Spread flaked coconut in pan.
Place all other ingredients in blender; blend well on high speed.
Carefully pour over coconut and make sure all coconut is moistened.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes, or until lightly browned and set like a custard.
Makes its own crust.

title: rolls
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and melted shortening.
Add salt and milk.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in water.
Lastly, add the flour.
Cover; let rise and make into rolls.
Let rise; bake in 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: porcupine beef meat balls
directions: Combine uncooked rice, ground meat, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup of the tomatoes.
Mix and form into 12 meat balls.
Place in a greased casserole.
Heat butter in skillet and lightly brown green pepper and onion.
Blend in flour and add remaining tomatoes. Slowly cook until thickened.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bob's mexican layer dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning in sour cream.
In a large Pyrex dish, layer the ingredients.
You can use as much or as little of each topping, depending upon your preference.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes (until cheese melts and it is hot throughout.)

title: amish pudding
directions: Whip sugar, flavoring and cream until fluffy.
Add graham crackers (crushed) and sliced bananas.
Cool and serve.

title: debbie's dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Beat pudding and milk for 3 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put half of pudding mixture on layer of graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and top with remaining pudding.
Top pudding with another layer of crackers.
Chill 2 hours.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat thoroughly after each.
Add flour and baking powder (1 spoonful at a time alternately with milk).
Add vanilla. Stir in crushed pineapple with juice and blend well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand a few minutes and remove from pan.
Frost with Pineapple Icing.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef, onion and green pepper.
Add eggs.
Add bread crumbs, enough to make it firm.
Shape into a loaf; put in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce on top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on a baking sheet, pinching all edges together.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and dressing mix together and spread over cooled crust. Cover with your choice of vegetables, meats or cheese.

title: fruit salad(can be used as dessert.)
directions: Drain the pineapple well; heat the juice with most of the sugar.
Add rest with the flour for thickening in water.
Boil, while stirring to keep it smooth, then add the beaten egg.
Boil a minute more and cool.
Then add the pineapple, grapes and oranges. Slice the bananas.
Sprinkle lemon juice over well; drain and add to mixture with marshmallows.
Mix lightly.
Coconut may be sprinkled over if liked.
Cover bowl well and chill to serve.

title: turtles
directions: You will need 3 or 4 cookie sheets lined with buttered wax paper.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave in 2 additional hours.
Do not open oven door until 3 hours have passed.
Cool and refrigerate.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: maggie's roquefort dressing
directions: At lowest speed, blend cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Stir in garlic powder and celery salt to taste.
Add green pepper and onion.
Important to use Kraft Roka and Best Foods brand for that smooth taste.
I use green onion instead of yellow onion.

title: jambalaya(low calorie)
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut into cubes; set aside.
Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Add onion and next 5 ingredients; saute until tender.
In a Dutch oven, add chicken, sauteed ingredients, sliced sausage, ground red and black pepper, water, bouillon, seasoning sauce and rice.
Bring to a
boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: basting sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until tender.
Just as onion begins to turn brown, add the remaining ingredients and simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: onion rings(indian style)
directions: Make a fairly thick batter with the ingredients.
Heat oil in a deep pan.
Dip each onion slice in the batter and deep-fry in oil over medium heat until slightly browned.
If you want it crispier, cook for 2 or 3 minutes more.
Remove from oil; drain and place in a dish, lined with paper towel.
Instead of slices, the onions can be made into rings and then dipped in batter and fried.

title: fruit and macaroni salad(the fruit enhances the taste of this salad.)
directions: Drain canned grapefruit sections.
(You may use juice instead of cold water when making jello.)
Make jello by dissolving first with hot water, then adding cold water or grapefruit juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in grapefruit sections and celery, then chill until firm.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.
Serves 6.

title: party mints
directions: Cream together cream cheese, salt and peppermint extract. Gradually add sugar until mixture is stiff enough to roll in a half-inch ball.
Flatten with a fork.
Decorate with a thinner mixture of the same.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Slice cabbage thin. Chop onions and add. Break noodles into small pieces. In skillet, melt margarine and brown noodles. Do not use noodle seasoning. When noodles are golden brown, add almonds and sesame seeds. Finish browning, watching carefully. Remove and set aside. Combine vinegar, oil, soy sauce and sugar in a pan and boil 1 minute. Let cool. Stir dressing well. Toss with salad greens and noodle mixture 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: almond poppy seed bread(makes a great dessert)
directions: Mix eggs, milk, oil and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix 1 to 2 minutes with a mixer.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato stuffed franks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Split franks lengthwise almost through. Lap open.
Combine potatoes and seasonings.
Spoon over split franks.
Top with cheese and another split frank.
Hold in place with toothpicks.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each serving.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well and let stand out of the refrigerator 8 to 12 hours. Refrigerate 3 to 5 days. Take out and add the same ingredients. Let stand for another 8 to 12 hours. It will be very bubbly. If going to make bread that day, use 1 cup of starter and put remaining starter in the refrigerator.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs, beating well.
Sift flour, baking powder and spices together.
Add to the other mixture alternately with milk.
Blend.
Add fruits and nuts which have been lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Soak tapioca overnight.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Break yeast into buttermilk.
Let stand a few minutes and add sugar and melted margarine, salt and beaten egg.
Sift flour with soda and baking powder and add to yeast mixture, alternating with whole wheat flour.
Add extra flour if needed.
Knead well and place in greased bowl.
Let rise to double in size.
Form into rolls and let double in size.
Bake in hot 400° oven until light brown on top.

title: garlic roasted new potatoes
directions: Place peeled potatoes in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine the margarine, water, garlic, salt and pepper.
Drizzle over potatoes.
Toss to coat.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring once.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes more or until the potatoes are tender and slightly browned.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage in bite-size pieces.
Peel and slice potatoes (about 1/4-inch thick).
If using new potatoes, wash and slice unpeeled potatoes.
Shred carrot.
Mix sausage, potatoes and carrot in a bowl.
Mix hot water and onion soup mix.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Put sausage mixture in dish and dot with butter.
If desired, salt and pepper top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more at 350°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine stems, broth, bay leaf and onion in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes and cook 3 minutes longer.
Strain and set aside.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Mix soda and nutmeg with 3 cups flour.
Add flour alternately.
Mix well.
Roll out and cut with cutters.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except chicken in saucepan.
Place over heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Place chicken in large baking pan.
Pour 1/2 of sauce over chicken and bake uncovered for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Baste with remaining sauce every 15 minutes during cooking.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage come to room temeperature.
Heat oven to 350°. With hands, combine sausage and cheese.
Add biscuit mix and blend in thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 30 minutes.
They freeze quite well.

title: spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in large frying pan.
Add finely chopped onion, green onions, minced garlic cloves and spices to the olive oil. Stir until onion is translucent.
Add sour cream to heated mixture.
Stir well.
When sauce is hot, add grated Mozzarella cheese.
Stir frequently.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add drained chopped clams and continue to stir.
Do not overcook or clams become tough.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Will freeze well.

title: quickie doughnuts
directions: Heat deep fat to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Beat vigorously 25 to 30 strokes.
Turn dough onto floured counter and knead about 10 times.
Roll out about 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter and place in hot fat.
Fry until golden brown, one or two minutes per side.
Remove from fat and drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, cinnamon and sugar or glaze with a thin chocolate icing.
Store in a large canister.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese.,
Pour into a hot greased pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Heat
oven
Melt
butter
in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. In	saucepan
heat	sugar
and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until it resembles fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir only until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn out on floured
surface.
Knead
until smooth.
Roll out to large rectangle,	1/4-inch
thick.
Sprinkle
cinnamon
over
dough. Sprinkle
apples over dough.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Dampen edge
of dough with a little water and seal.
Slice dough into 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Place in dish with melted butter. Pour sugar syrup around rolls.
It looks like too much water, but dough will absorb syrup.	Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: heidelberg soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender.
Add cream of celery soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Scoop out avocado after cutting lengthwise. Mash with fork until smooth.
Add milk or lemon juice to prevent discoloring. Cut and mince onion, dice green pepper and tomato and add smidge of salt.
Mix.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: microwave cream cheese dip
directions: Place cream cheese in a microwavable bowl.
Strain the Ro-Tel tomatoes of juice and place the remainder of contents with the cream cheese.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, then mix and stir. Serve this dip with chips or vegetables.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice mix using package directions. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Put into 400° oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: holiday aroma
directions: Mix water with cinnamon sticks, cloves, rind of orange and lemon and almond extract.
Simmer on stove.
Can add more when necessary.
Gardening petals can be added for looks if desired.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla together. Then add M&M's and flour.
Bake at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger over medium heat; add onion and lower heat. Add tomato soup and juice from kidney beans.
Stir in chili powder, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour, then add beans and simmer for 1/2 hour longer.
Serves 4.

title: cheddar crispy wafers
directions: Cream margarine.
Add flour, salt and baking powder slowly. Mix well.
Stir cereal and cheese in with a spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using a fork, flatten and make crisscross mark.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: new england cottage bread
directions: Bake
in
a
casserole, measure into mixing bowl:
warm water, add, stirring to dissolve 2 packages active dry yeast. Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, and 1/2 the flour.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth, mix in rest of flour thoroughly. Cover,
let rise
in a warm place until doubled (30 minutes). Pour
half into greased pan 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, half into 1
1/2 quart baking dish.
Let rise.
Brush with melted shortening.
Bake
until brown at 350° for 40 to 59 minutes.
Cover for
soft
crust,
brush with
butter and leave uncovered for crunchy crust.

title: fisherman's stew
directions: Rinse fish and set aside.
In a heavy pan, melt butter and cook celery, onion and garlic until tender.
Add sauce and rest of seasonings.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add water and uncooked spaghetti.
Mix, cover and cook until spaghetti is firm and tender (al dente).
Add fish.
Cover and simmer until fish flakes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in 3-quart pan.
Add onion; saute 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add potatoes and clam juice; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are tender. Stir in soup and sour cream.
Gradually add milk.
Add clams, salt, pepper and parsley.
Stir until clams are hot.
DO NOT BOIL!!
Add dash of garlic salt and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Serves 5.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken breast into half.
Wipe dry; remove skin and excess fat.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except margarine and cornflakes.
Stir well.
Add chicken.
Make sure each piece is covered well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Remove chicken pieces and blot off with paper towel.
Dip each piece in melted margarine.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.

title: homemade chicken and noodles
directions: Beat together water, eggs and salt. Add flour; beat.

Work in 1 more cup of flour. Divide dough in thirds. Roll out each third on HEAVILY floured surface. Fold each section and put aside. Then stack layers (with lots of flour in between) and roll up like a jelly roll. Take a sharp knife (or electric knife) and slice very thin. Spread out noodles to dry for 3 to 4 hours. Sprinkle noodles (and stir often) into rolling boil of chicken broth (at least 3 cans with an extra can on reserve if it gets too thick). Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour (with lid). Add diced chicken.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Beat well the flour, sugar, shortening, salt, cocoa, baking soda and milk.
Stir in baking powder, unbeaten eggs and vanilla. Beat all together.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes. Remove and cool on racks.
Fill and top with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: lemony basil mushroom soup
directions: In 5 quart Dutch oven, saute onions, mushrooms, celery, carrots and garlic in margarine until tender. Stir in water, chicken broth, cream of chicken soup, basil, pepper, lemon juice, wild and regular rice. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until wild rice is tender. Garnish each serving with lemon slice and Parmesan cheese. 16 (1 c.) servings.

title: corn-clam chowder chablis(serves 4 or 5)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Chop onions very fine and cook in 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings until soft but not browned.
Add all other ingredients, except crackers, and bring just to boil.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Crumble crackers
in bottom of soup bowls.
Pour in hot soup and serve immediately.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put okra, carrots and onions in pot.
Add shortening; cook about 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper; cook about 40 minutes more.
Add tomato sauce about the last 5 minutes of cooking.
Add 1 can of corn and mix well.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and place in 2 pint jars.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Place 1 teaspoon dill seed, 2 garlic cloves and 1 hot pepper in each jar.
Pour boiling mixture into jars to cook okra and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 pints.

title: steak pigs in blankets
directions: Salt and pepper steak to taste.
Slice steak in rectangular pieces 2-inches wide and as long as 1/2 slice of bacon.
Lay bacon on steak.
Add 1 piece of onion and 1 piece of carrot.
Roll up and pin with toothpick.
Panfry in 3 tablespoons butter.
Brown on all sides and add any leftover onions and carrots.
Cover with water and simmer covered for 1 hour until tender.
This is great served with mashed potatoes!

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, pecans and flour and press in long (9 x 2 x 13-inch) dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned; let cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust, let cool and firm.
Mix instant pudding and spread on first layer; let firm.
Top with Cool Whip; decorate, if desired.
Keep in freezer; take out 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a bowl. Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden. Remove from sheet immediately. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage gravy(s.o.s.; an army term)
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until lightly browned, pour off any grease.
Add butter then milk, flour and onions and stir until mixture is smooth and has thickened.
Add paprika and parsley just before serving over toast or biscuits.
Serves 4.

title: fisherman's macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
Drain fish liquid into 1-pint cup.
Add enough milk to make 2 cups.
Flake fish.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour, seasoned salt, instant onion, pepper and mustard.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add 1 cup of cheese; stir until melted and blended. Fold in pasta, fish, Worcestershire sauce, sour cream and peas. Turn into greased pan.
Cook in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti mediterranean
directions: In saute pan, cook shrimp, garlic, parsley, butter and oil at medium heat until butter is melted and garlic is glazed.
Take off heat and add wine, white pepper, crabmeat, clams and clam juice.
Continue to cook at medium heat until shrimp are cooked. Fill an 8-quart pot with 6 quarts of water and salt.
Bring water to boil and add pasta.
Cook until al dente.
Strain and place on a large platter.
Spoon sauce on top.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Crush garlic and brown in small amount of oil.
Brown chicken. Add vinegar and water; simmer about 45 minutes.
Shake in soy sauce after approximately the first 30 minutes.
I use thighs and legs, cut in half.

title: freezer french toast(serves 12)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl and mix until well blended.
Place muffins on rimmed cookie sheet.
Slowly pour mixture over muffins, turning to coat both sides completely.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Flash freeze and then place muffins in a freezer bag until ready to serve.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and salt to boil, then cool.
Mix vegetables and pour liquid mixture over them.
Add mayonnaise when serving.

title: dutch potato casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Combine all ingredients and turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Let broccoli soften enough to break apart.
Spray deep casserole dish with Pam.
Mix all ingredients and pour into dish. Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick delicious brownies
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Mix thoroughly.
Remove pan from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Spread batter in a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring to boil pie filling and water.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple that is partially drained, nuts and Coke.
Pour into serving dish and refrigerate.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Spoon the pie filling into the cake in 16 spots evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Greens are best when young and tender.
Select those which are crisp, tender and have a bright color.
Allow about 2 pounds of greens to serve 4.
Wash greens several times and break off any tough stems.
Put bacon grease or cooking oil in a large pot with the greens.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper.
The water that clings to the greens after washing them may be enough liquid.
If not, add a little more.
Using a sharp knife, chop the greens before serving.

title: somebody's mother's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Add boiling water; stir constantly, bring to a boil.
Add sugar and corn syrup; stir until all is dissolved.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients together until done.
Remove from burner and add the grated cheese, beaten eggs and dash of red pepper.
Stir well.
Put into a greased baking dish with cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joe bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Mix tomato sauce, ketchup and mustard with hamburger. Pour in pie plate. Mix Bisquick, milk and egg and pour on top. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas butter fudge
directions: Place sugar, milk, butter and salt in large saucepan.

Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water (236° on candy thermometer). Remove from heat and place pan in cold water.
Do not stir or beat until cooled to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy.
Quickly fold in nuts and cherries.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Let stand at room temperature until firm.
Cut into squares and decorate with candied fruit.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place apple slices in bottom.
Mix brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and oleo well.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: apple mallow yams
directions: Grease oblong pan with vegetable oil.
Pour yams evenly in pan followed by apple slices and nuts, then sprinkle brown sugar over apples, yams and nuts.
Place pats of butter over brown sugar. Bake at 350° until apples are tender and brown sugar bubbles. When baked, cover apples, yams and nuts with marshmallows.
Put back into oven until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: peel a pound soup(diet)
directions: Cut all ingredients in bite-size pieces.
Cover with water and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
One tablespoon grated cheese or 1 package dry onion soup mix may be added.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Combine cranberry juice cocktail and pectin in a large saucepan.
Stir over high heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Stir in sugar and return to a full boil; boil hard for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Skim off foam with a metal spoon and pour quickly into sterilized jelly glasses, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal immediately with 1/8-inch layer of hot paraffin.
Yield: 7 pints.

title: black walnut cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, place in order listed, except confectioners sugar.
Beat slowly until blended.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until rich and golden brown and pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool in pan on rack for 5 minutes.
Gently loosen and invert on rack.
Turn top side up and cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar stirred through a sifter.

title: rotel dip
directions: Melt cheese in top of a double boiler.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and blend thoroughly.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Mix and set aside the flour, baking soda and salt.
Heat molasses, shortening and sugar until all are dissolved.
Combine beaten eggs with milk, vanilla and oil of cinnamon.
Add to molasses mixture.
Make a hole in the flour mixture.
Pour the liquid in slowly.
Mix until the mixture is a stiff dough.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Roll out a small ball of dough on a floured board until it is no more than 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out circle of dough in shape of a pie pan.
Place circles on cookie sheets and bake at 350° until brown.
Let cool.
Place in stacks using applesauce between layers.
Let stand for 36 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in greased casserole.
Add topping of 1 cup crushed corn flakes mixed with 2 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: crab delight fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini according to package.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet until lightly browned.
Add half and half, crab and pepper.
Heat 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Toss crab sauce with fettucini.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: portuguese dressing for green salad
directions: Put all in a tightly covered jar and shake until blended and emulsified.
Pour over mixed greens garnished with sliced tomatoes, red onion rings and sliced black olives.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix cornflakes and margarine together.
Put half of mixture in bottom of an oblong pan.
Put cabbage and onion over this.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, milk and cheese.
Pour over cabbage.
Put remaining cornflake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Place ingredients in an electric blender.
Blend until mixture becomes paste-like or speadable.
It may be necessary to add more peanut oil.
The ingredients must be blended for several minutes. Store in tightly covered container.
Homemade peanut butter will separate on standing; stir before using.
You may leave out the sugar and salt, if desired.

title: cashew egg noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; saute celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Add cream of chicken and mushroom soup.
Add as many cashews as desired.
Mix all together, except the butter and bread crumbs.
Mix them and pour over filling. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered, then 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: speedy cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Makes six 6-ounce servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Roll in nuts before serving.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Melt caramel candy and milk (slowly).
Mix in pecans.
Drop onto greased foil.
Melt chocolate (slowly).
After candy has cooled well, dip down into melted chocolate.
Drop again onto greased foil to cool.

title: onion corn bread
directions: Saute onions in butter for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add the sour cream, salt, and 1/2 cup cheese to onion mixture and set aside.
Mix together the egg, milk, muffin mix, corn and pepper sauce.
Spread muffin mix in an 8-inch square greased pan.
Put the sour cream mixture on top.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 30-35 minutes.
Let set before cutting.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make sure to mix them well. Makes 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked ziti with vegetables
directions: Saute peppers in oil for 5 minutes.
Remove and set aside. Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms for several minutes.
Break up tomatoes and add to skillet; add tomato sauce, wine, basil, salt, pepper and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add spinach and corn; cook until spinach wilts.
Combine ziti, tomato mixture, Ricotta and 2/3 of peppers and spoon into prepared casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Garnish with remaining peppers.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: You will also need nonstick spray coating.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and butter over rhubarb.
Blend the rest and spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Good with ice cream.

title: colorful vegetable hors d'oeuvre
directions: Line an 11 x 15-inch pan with crescent rolls.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley mix; spread mix on top of rolls.
Cover with thinly sliced green peppers, broccoli flowerets, shredded carrots and shredded cheese last.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pudding mix and pumpkin pie spice in small mixer bowl.
Blend with wire whisk or electric mixer (low) for 1 minute.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups of the Cool Whip.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple; let set and add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Heat molasses and add soda (mixture will foam).
Add to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat softened cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in real lemon juice and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust. Drizzle chocolate syrup over pie. Gently swirl with spoon. Chill 4 hours or until set. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, separating and breaking up the noodles. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seeds and membranes.
Precook in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
(For crisper peppers, omit precooking).
Generously sprinkle inside of peppers with salt.
In skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in croutons, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms, tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spoon into peppers.
Place in 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.
Contains 212 calories per serving.
Serves 8.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix spinach, eggs and bacon bits into bowl.
In saucepan, combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and mustard.
Heat to boiling. Pour hot dressing over spinach mixture; mix well and serve.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil and then remove from heat. Add peanut butter and cornflakes. Mix well. Spoon out mixture onto wax paper.

title: old german pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except milk.
Add milk last.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 pies.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown chicken.
Add wine, water and oregano.
Cook until chicken is done.
Add mushrooms.
Serve over rice.

title: pork adobo
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients.
Mix them all up in a pot. Simmer on medium heat for about 45 minutes, until water is half gone.
Do not stir.
Add potato.
Let it simmer until cooked. When water is dry and oil starts to sizzle, stir and serve.

title: mama's good soup
directions: Mix all in one large soup pot. Let simmer at least 1 hour. Serve with hot bread.

title: breakfast bake(serves 6)
directions: Break up and cook sausage; drain.
Beat together eggs, salt and mustard.
Grease baking dish.
Layer bread, cheese and sausage.
Cover with egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until thickened (about 45 to 60 minutes).

title: pink lady salad
directions: Optional:
Substitute orange jello and mandarin oranges, or your choice of fruit.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo until transparent.
Add mushroom soup, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Stir; add cooked rice and mix in. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Prepare the sour cream, mix with the milk according to directions on package.
Stir flour into sour cream.
Add to the shrimp mixture and let simmer a few more minutes.
Spoon into a casserole dish.
Serve or let cool.
Seal secure and freeze.
To serve, thaw and bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.
Garnish with chives or parsley.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in saucepan over low heat; stir in vanilla and remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin in a saucepan over low heat.
Dip each ball into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper to cool.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: barley and mushroom bake
directions: Add olive oil in large skillet.
Saute onions and mushrooms until tender.
Add barley and saute 4 minutes or until barley is lightly browned. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish, sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Add water, bouillon and pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Gently stir in parsley.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute medium onion with margarine.
Mix all ingredients and add onion.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients. May add a little milk, if too stiff. Shape into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve warm.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat milk and sugar.
Pour over beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla. Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: potatoes ala elegant
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Very good.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to package directions and drain.
In large saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Blend in flour, salt and pepper; gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and mixture begins to boil.
Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.
In 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan, stir together pasta and cheese sauce.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: old fashion dumplings
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a hole in the center and pour 1 cup boiling broth.
Mix with fork.
Use more broth if needed.
Put dough onto a floured board or waxed paper.
Knead 2 or 3 times, then roll out with floured rolling pin. Cut into strips and drop into boiling broth.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling and cold water.
Chill well until thick, not set.
Stir in cranberry sauce, celery and nuts.
Pour into mold or pan and chill until set.

title: cherry buttermilk cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt gradually with buttermilk.
Add chopped nuts, cherries and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool and frost with icing.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour with salt and pepper; pound into meat.
In family skillet, melt shortening over medium heat, about 3 minutes. Do not allow shortening to smoke.
Brown steak for 5 minutes per side.
Add mushrooms, onions, green pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer over low heat, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased, 9-inch pie pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: wine cheese rolls
directions: Blend
cheeses	thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill until firm enough to mold into logs or one ball.
Freeze or refrigerate.
Makes 4 logs.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
mixing well.
Shape loosely into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about 100.

title: easy chicken pie for a crowd
directions: In
a
large
casserole
dish,	layer
chicken, drained canned vegetables, soups mixed with chicken broth and, on top, mix Bisquick
with
milk and pour on mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake
at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until brown on top and
crust
is
done.
Let rest 5 or 10 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers with collard greens
directions: Wash and julienne collard greens. Place in large saucepan. Season with salt and pepper.
Add oil.
Stir.
Cook on low heat one hour or until tender.
Add water if needed.
Cut peppers in half.
Remove seeds.
Blanch in hot water about 10 minutes. Remove from water.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
Stuff peppers with collard greens.
Garnish with diced carrots and turnips.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 85 calories, fat 3 g (27 cal or 31% of total calories), sat fat <1 g (<5% of total calories), carb 13 g, protein 4 g, chol 0 mg and sodium 130 mg.

title: cold taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Put in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put bean dip on top of that.
Begin layering the rest of the ingredients, beginning with the ground beef. Sprinkle taco seasoning, shredded cheese, taco seasoning, green peppers, taco seasoning, etc.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shepherd's pie casserole
directions: Make mashed potatoes according to package directions.
Brown ground meat; drain.
Saute onions.
Layer ground meat, green beans and corn.
Pour tomato soup over all.
Top these layers with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle potatoes with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown around edges and bubbly.

title: southwestern bean soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook bacon until crisp;
remove to paper towel to drain.
Crumble and set aside.
In the drippings, saute the onion and celery;
sprinkle with the garlic powder. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add beans, salsa, broth, parsley and baco9n;
bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste with hot pepper sauce.
Ladle into bowls and top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shenandoah valley apple cake
directions: Beat together the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla for about 3 minutes.
Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Stir in apples. Combine walnuts with 1 tablespoon flour, if desired.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Place a 4 to 5 pound stewing hen in kettle with enough water to cover and cook gently until tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Let cool in broth.
Remove meat from bone and cut in bite-size pieces.
Place cut chicken in bottom of 8 1/2 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover the chicken with gravy made by thickening the broth with flour.
This will take about 2 cups gravy.

Cut up about 3/4 loaf of bread into cubes and make a dressing, seasoning with salt and pepper using onion and celery according to taste. Moisten with chicken broth, according to whether you want wet or dry dressing.
Place the dressing on top of chicken and gravy and bake in a moderately hot oven until the gravy is bubbling and the dressing is slightly browned.
This will take about 30 minutes. This dish can be prepared the day before it is needed and placed in the refrigerator until time to bake.
This will serve 10 to 12 persons.
Any remaining broth can be used to make gravy to serve on the dressing.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water.
Add nuts; mix and add sugar and salt.
Mix well and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Stir nuts every 10 minutes.;

title: pork chops and spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in hot oil in a large skillet for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove rice and set aside.
Add pork chops to skillet and brown on both sides. Combine rice, tomato and next 5 ingredients. Spoon over pork chops.
Add water; cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until chops are tender. Serves 4.

title: date loaf
directions: Cup up dates and sprinkle the soda over them.
Then pour boiling water over and stir.
Let cool and then add other ingredients; bake 1 hour.

title: mexican fried ice cream
directions: Put four parts sugar to 1 part cinnamon in dish.
Put Team Flakes in Ziploc bag and mash.
Take large ball of ice cream and roll in sugar mixture, then in Team Flakes.
Put in freezer until hard.
Drop in deep fat fryer 3 to 4 seconds only.
Drain 5 seconds on towel.
Serve with whipped cream and cherry.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar and peanut butter. Slowly add the milk.
Blend 8 ounces of the Cool Whip in by hand. Pour into the graham cracker crust and place in freezer several hours to chill.
Before serving, top with remaining Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate sauce, then sprinkle with chopped salted peanuts.
Makes one delicious dessert; enjoy!

title: italian hunter's stew
directions: In large Dutch oven, heat salad oil.
Brown chuck lightly on all sides.
Add garlic and onions and saute well, turning frequently.
Now stir in tomato paste, flour, chili powder, oregano, rosemary, seasoned salt, tomatoes and parsley.
Add 1 cup water; simmer, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Skim off fat, if necessary.
Now add carrots.
Simmer until carrots are tender.

title: no roll pie crust dough
directions: Cut into flour the salt and shortening until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle 2 to 3 tablespoons cold water into flour mixture, mixing lightly with fork after each addition until pastry is just moist enough to hold together.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Flute edge.
Cover with plastic wrap to keep moist.
Makes a 9-inch crust.

title: serbian cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in a shallow 4-quart casserole dish.
Pour milk over, sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Cover; bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until crumbs are lightly browned and cabbage is tender. Delicious served with ham.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir peanuts, flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in a bowl.
Stir in margarine.
Press in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spoon Marshmallow Creme over hot layer.
Let stand 1 minute; spread evenly.
Drizzle topping over Marshmallow Creme.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups salted peanuts.
Bake until golden brown (20 minutes). Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat 3 eggs.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, 2 to 3 tablespoons flour and 1 can crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir well.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg as desired.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a pan (12 x 12-inch) or an iron pan (the bigger the pan, the thinner the bread).
Leave half of margarine in pan.
Add the rest to cornbread mix.
Mix all ingredients, except half margarine.
Add margarine.
Pour into pan with rest of margarine in it.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: italian steak sandwiches
directions: Melt 2 tablespoonfuls butter in frying pan.
Brown onion slices in butter slowly until tender.
Combine tomato sauce and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Stir in 1 teaspoonful butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Quickly brown steak in pan with onion.
Slice rolls; sprinkle with olive oil.
Place 2 tablespoonfuls of sauce in each roll; add steak and onion.
Top with remaining sauce.
Garnish with pickle slices and additional oregano.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Slice apples to fill pie pan.
Transfer to bowl and mix with sugar and cinnamon.
Line pie pans with pastry.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 tablespoon of flour in bottom of pan and stir with fingers.
Mix apples with 3/4 cup of sugar and remaining flour. Pile apples in pie pan and dot with butter.
Put on top crust and crimp.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: clam walnut roll
directions: Beat together softened cream cheese and drained minced clams. Blend in lemon juice, chopped onion, salt and garlic salt.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the chopped walnuts.
Chill.
Turn out onto waxed paper.
Shape into 2 rolls similar to a stick of butter.
Roll in remaining chopped walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: good granola
directions: Mix the oatmeal, wheat germ, coconut, sunflower seed, powdered milk and cinnamon.
Add the honey, oil and vanilla; mix well. Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, cream the butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple with juice.
Cube the bread slices and fold into pineapple mixture. Spoon mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Serve warm as a side dish or dessert.

title: salmon peaches
directions: Bake salmon with wine at 400° for 5 minutes.
Place salmon on plate and top with peaches.
Mix wine, butter and cream of tarragon until sauce thickens.
Spoon over salmon and peaches.
